WEBVTT

00:01.790 --> 00:02.870
Alex: IT ALL STARTED SIX MONTHS
AGO AT THE FBI ACADEMY.

00:02.880 --> 00:05.872
YOU WERE WILLING TO DIE TODAY
FOR EVERYONE IN THAT ROOM.

00:05.880 --> 00:07.529
YOU SAID YOUR SON CAME AT YOU
FROM BEHIND.

00:07.540 --> 00:09.383
HOW CAN YOU BE CERTAIN
IT WAS HIM?

00:09.390 --> 00:11.460
I NEVER SAID "I LOVE YOU"
WHEN I REALLY WANTED TO.

00:11.470 --> 00:12.880
I'VE NEVER SAID IT AT ALL.

00:12.890 --> 00:14.505
Caleb:
YOU SLEPT WITH MY DAD.

00:14.510 --> 00:16.626
I CAN'T IMAGINE HOW YOUR MOM'S
GONNA FEEL WHEN SHE FINDS OUT.

00:16.630 --> 00:18.177
SHE ALREADY KNOWS.
YEAH, I TOLD HER.

00:18.180 --> 00:19.761
I'M THE ONE
WHO PLANNED GRAND CENTRAL.

00:19.770 --> 00:22.011
SOMEBODY STOLE MY PLANS
AND USED THEM FOR THEMSELVES.

00:22.020 --> 00:23.760
WE KNOW THAT THE BOMBER
PLANNED THEIR A'l'I'ACK

00:23.770 --> 00:25.431
AROUND THE DEMOCRATIC
NATIONAL CONVENTION.

00:25.440 --> 00:28.807
MY SENTENCING IS IN 23 HOURS.
WE NEED TO FIND THIS BOMB FAST.

00:30.360 --> 00:32.851
Simon:
YOU EVER WANT TO PUSH A BUTTON
AND MAKE IT ALL GO AWAY?

00:32.860 --> 00:35.021
EVERYONE YOU EVER LOVED
AND LOST,

00:35.030 --> 00:38.102
EVERYTHING THAT EVER
HURT YOU -- JUST ONE BUTTON?

00:38.110 --> 00:39.202
NO MORE FIGHTING.

00:39.210 --> 00:40.325
NO MORE REGRETS.

00:40.330 --> 00:41.820
NO MORE NOISE.

00:41.830 --> 00:43.957
BLOW IT ALL UP
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

00:48.460 --> 00:51.964
NOW THAT CONFIRMED TERRORIST
ALEX PARRISH IS BEHIND BARS,

00:51.970 --> 00:55.258
NEW YORK CITY
IS ONCE AGAIN OPENING ITS DOORS

00:55.260 --> 00:58.752
AND TAKING STOCK OF WHAT HAS
AND WHAT HAS NOT CHANGED.

00:58.760 --> 00:59.977
IN JUST A FEW HOURS,

00:59.980 --> 01:01.595
THE DEMOCRATIC
NATIONAL CONVENTION

01:01.600 --> 01:03.511
WILL BE BACK UNDER WAY.

01:03.520 --> 01:05.385
TENS OF THOUSANDS ARE EXPECTED,

01:05.390 --> 01:07.221
INCLUDING
THE PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE

01:07.230 --> 01:09.482
AND HIS RUMORED PICK
FOR VICE PRESIDENT,

01:09.490 --> 01:11.526
SENATOR CLAIRE HAAS.

01:11.530 --> 01:13.236
OTHER LUMINARIES
WILL ALSO BE THERE,

01:13.240 --> 01:16.232
PRESENTING AWARDS TO
THE TOP LEADERSHIP OF THE FBI,

01:16.240 --> 01:19.027
HOPING TO SHOW
THAT NEW YORK MAY BE DOWN

01:19.030 --> 01:21.328
BUT SHE IS NOT OUT.

01:21.330 --> 01:23.958
YOU'RE WASTING TIME DOWN HERE
PRETENDING TO INTERVIEW ME.

01:23.960 --> 01:25.404
Miranda:
IT'S NOT A WASTE OF TIME.

01:25.410 --> 01:27.366
IT'S WHY YOU'RE STILL
IN THE COMMAND CENTER WITH US.

01:27.370 --> 01:28.689
WE HAVE TO KEEP UP
APPEARANCES.

01:28.700 --> 01:29.962
THERE'S STILL A BOMBER
OUT THERE.

01:29.970 --> 01:31.790
WITH ME IN CUSTODY,
NO ONE'S LOOKING FOR THEM.

01:31.800 --> 01:33.620
THE FBI's
ALWAYS ON ALERT.

01:33.630 --> 01:36.258
WHAT, THE STANDARD "IF YOU SEE
SOMETHING, SAY SOMETHING"?

01:36.260 --> 01:38.160
THAT'S NOT
GONNA CUT IT HERE, LIAM.

01:38.170 --> 01:40.593
WHATEVER THE FBI IS DOING,
IT'S NOT ENOUGH.

01:40.600 --> 01:42.761
THE REAL BOMBER IS
INSIDE THE BUREAU.

01:42.770 --> 01:45.477
IT GIVES THEM SPECIAL ACCESS,
KNOWLEDGE OF PROCEDURES.

01:45.480 --> 01:47.175
IT ALLOWS THEM
TO MANIPULATE THE SYSTEM.

01:47.180 --> 01:48.169
THEY CAN DO WHAT--
YOUR --

01:48.180 --> 01:50.148
ALEX, YOUR GUILTY PLEA
ALLOWED YOU

01:50.150 --> 01:52.892
TO BE REMANDED TO FBI CUSTODY
FOR 24 HOURS.

01:52.900 --> 01:55.983
AFI'ER THAT, WE HAVE TO
DELIVER YOU TO FEDERAL PRISON.

01:55.990 --> 02:00.404
WHICH MEANS IF WE DON'T FIND
A SECOND BOMB OR BOMBER

02:00.410 --> 02:02.822
IN THE NEXT FOUR HOURS,
YOU'LL BE SERVING

02:02.830 --> 02:04.536
A LIFE SENTENCE
FOR A CRIME YOU DIDN'T COMMIT.

02:04.540 --> 02:06.610
I HAVE A FRIEND
IN THE C.I.A.

02:06.620 --> 02:08.281
HE'S WILLING TO EXTRACT YOU
OUT OF THE COUNTRY.

02:08.290 --> 02:10.451
NO.
I'M NOT RUNNING AGAIN.

02:10.460 --> 02:12.917
NOT WITH SO MANY PEOPLE'S LIVES
IN DANGER.

02:12.920 --> 02:14.626
LOOK, YOU NEED
TO FIND THAT BOMB NOW.

02:14.630 --> 02:16.245
AND YOU NEED MORE MANPOWER
TO DO IT.

02:16.250 --> 02:17.410
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

02:17.420 --> 02:19.593
THE ENTIRE TOP TIER
OF THE BUREAU'S IN TOWN

02:19.600 --> 02:22.091
TO STAND ONSTAGE AND SHOW
THE WORLD THAT WE PREVAILED.

02:22.100 --> 02:24.341
AND NO ONE BUT A HANDFUL
OF PEOPLE KNOW THAT WE HAVEN'T.

02:24.350 --> 02:27.672
THE BOMB SQUAD IS SWEEPING THE
CONVENTION CENTER FOR TONIGHT

02:27.680 --> 02:29.682
AND THE DONOR DINNER
AT THE HOTEL BEFORE.

02:29.690 --> 02:31.226
IF THERE'S SOMETHING
TO BE FOUND,

02:31.230 --> 02:32.436
TH EY'LL FIND IT.

02:32.440 --> 02:34.180
"IF"?

02:34.190 --> 02:35.521
ARE YOU DOUBTING ME NOW?

02:37.820 --> 02:40.482
WE HAVE TO GO BACK UPSTAIRS.
WE'VE BEEN GONE TOO LONG.

02:40.490 --> 02:41.650
WE'LL BE BACK.

02:44.240 --> 02:45.446
[ DOOR CLANKS ]

02:47.580 --> 02:49.582
[ POUNDING ON DOOR]

02:49.590 --> 02:53.242
OH, MAN. THEY REALLY DON'T CARE
ABOUT HOLIDAYS HERE, DO THEY?

02:53.250 --> 02:56.128
CHRISTMAS WAS LAST WEEK.
IT'S BACK-TO-WORK TIME.

02:56.130 --> 02:57.279
[ SIGHS ]

02:57.290 --> 02:59.508
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU,
BUT FOR A LOT OF PEOPLE,

02:59.510 --> 03:00.556
NEW YEAR'S EVE
IS SPECIAL.

03:00.560 --> 03:02.050
WHY?

03:02.060 --> 03:04.790
IT'S JUST THE NEXT DAY
IN A LONG LINE OF DAYS

03:04.800 --> 03:08.008
UNTIL YOU DIE
A TERRIBLY SAD, LONELY DEATH,

03:08.010 --> 03:09.898
SURROUNDED WITH PEOPLE
YOU DON'T EVEN REMEMBER.

03:11.190 --> 03:12.646
OF COURSE
I LOVE NEW YEAR'S!

03:12.650 --> 03:13.969
LET'S REVOLT.
DO YOU WANT TO GO FIRST?

03:13.980 --> 03:15.390
YOU'RE CRAZY.

03:15.400 --> 03:17.186
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

03:17.190 --> 03:19.010
IT IS LITERALLY
FREEZING OUTSIDE.

03:19.020 --> 03:20.817
I DON'T KNOW
HOW THEY EXPECT US TO RUN

03:20.820 --> 03:23.072
THE YELLOW BRICK ROAD
IN 10-DEGREE WEATHER

03:23.080 --> 03:25.731
OR PRACTICE SHARPSHOOTING
WITH FROSTBITE.

03:25.740 --> 03:28.231
WHINE ABOUT THE COLD
LIKE A LITTLE LATOSA?

03:31.630 --> 03:33.370
LITTLE-KNOWN ACADEMY TRADITION.

03:33.380 --> 03:35.450
IF YOU'RE IN A CLASS
THAT HAS HOLIDAYS,

03:35.460 --> 03:36.825
YOU DESERVE
HOLIDAY CHEER!

03:36.830 --> 03:38.411
CHRISTMAS WAS SATURDAY.

03:38.420 --> 03:40.331
WHERE DO YOU THINK
WE GOT THESE COOKIES FROM?

03:40.340 --> 03:42.638
BEER FOR BREAKFAST?

03:42.640 --> 03:44.926
WHAT WERE YOU EXPECTING --
BELLINIS, PRINCESS PEACH?

03:44.930 --> 03:47.296
THE FACT
THAT THIS IS EVEN HAPPENING

03:47.300 --> 03:48.597
IS A CHRISTMAS MIRACLE.

03:48.600 --> 03:50.101
THERE'S CIDER, TOO.

03:50.110 --> 03:51.259
MMM.

03:51.270 --> 03:52.931
[ COUGHS ]

03:52.940 --> 03:55.340
OH! MAKE THAT RUM
WITH A CIDER AFI'ERTASTE.

03:55.350 --> 03:57.932
YOU KNOW WHAT -- AT LEAST
WE GET THE LONG WEEKEND OFF.

03:57.940 --> 03:59.407
IS YOUR MOM EXCITED
YOU'RE COMING HOME?

03:59.410 --> 04:00.445
SHE SAYS SHE IS.

04:00.450 --> 04:01.815
WE HAVE SO MUCH
TO TALK ABOUT.

04:01.820 --> 04:03.651
I DON'T KNOW
IF THREE DAYS WILL CUT IT.

04:03.660 --> 04:05.150
WHAT,
ARE YOU GOING TO AUGUSTA?

04:05.160 --> 04:07.560
SAVANNAH. NO, MY SORORITY
SISTERS ARE THROWING A THING.

04:07.570 --> 04:08.946
YOU WOULD HATE IT.

04:08.950 --> 04:11.032
IT'S EXACTLY
WHAT YOU PICTURE IT WOULD BE.

04:11.040 --> 04:13.827
KWANZAA-CO IS GONNA BE
THE MOST FUN UNTIL 2016.

04:13.830 --> 04:15.957
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I HAVE TO LEAVE IN AN HOUR.

04:15.960 --> 04:17.996
I'M SURE YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
A NICE TIME AT HOME.

04:18.000 --> 04:19.831
WELL, I'M GLAD THAT YOU THINK
THAT, KIMMY SCHMIDT,

04:19.840 --> 04:21.501
BUT "AMERICAN BEAUTY"
IS A ROM-COM

04:21.510 --> 04:23.501
COMPARED TO THE HOLIDAYS
WITH MY FAMILY.

04:23.510 --> 04:25.250
YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANT
TO SPEND NEW YEAR'S

04:25.260 --> 04:26.466
WITH A DOZEN FBI AGENTS

04:26.470 --> 04:29.041
AND A SENATOR DRUNK ON PUNCH
AND WHITE PRIVILEGE?

04:29.050 --> 04:31.689
[ LAUGHS ] YEAH,
I'VE SPENT THE PAST 15 YEARS

04:31.690 --> 04:33.840
THINKING A CON ARTIST
IS MY SISTER.

04:33.850 --> 04:36.683
I'D REALLY RATHER NOT BE AT
A TABLE WITH A FAMILY RIGHT NOW.

04:36.690 --> 04:38.305
EVEN IF IT'S WITH
THE LANNISTERS?

04:38.310 --> 04:40.358
'CAUSE THAT'S KIND OF
WHAT IT'S LIKE.

04:40.360 --> 04:43.659
IF YOU NEED ME, I'M ONLY
A 20-MINUTE RIDE AWAY, OKAY?

04:43.660 --> 04:44.524
THANK YOU.

04:44.530 --> 04:47.351
KEG STANDS!

04:47.360 --> 04:51.069
[ ALL CHEERING ]

04:51.080 --> 04:52.991
SOME BOYS NEVER GROW UP.

04:56.870 --> 04:59.373
Alex:
YOU MISS SIMON, HUH?

04:59.380 --> 05:01.120
DON'T TELL ANYONE...

05:01.130 --> 05:02.916
but I really
miss Ryan, too.

05:02.920 --> 05:04.467
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:04.470 --> 05:07.712
I GUESS NO MATTER WHO YOU ARE
OR WHAT YOU BELIEVE IN,

05:07.720 --> 05:10.518
THE HOLIDAYS
WILL STILL GET YOU DOWN.

05:10.520 --> 05:12.636
HAVE A SAFE TRIP
BACK HOME.

05:12.640 --> 05:14.631
YOU TOO, RAINA.

05:14.640 --> 05:16.631
OH, OH, AY-OH

05:16.640 --> 05:18.471
OH, OH, AY-OH

05:19.650 --> 05:20.776
EVERYTHING OKAY?

05:21.820 --> 05:23.526
YEAH. YEAH.

05:23.530 --> 05:25.020
IS THIS ABOUT CHARLIE?

05:25.030 --> 05:26.770
I TOLD YOU ONCE I HAD
ANY REAL INFORMATION,

05:26.780 --> 05:28.190
I WOULD BRING IT TO YOU.

05:28.200 --> 05:29.997
I KNOW
WHEN I'M BEING HANDLED.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.241
AGENTS CAN'T WORK CASES
INVOLVING FAMILY MEMBERS.

05:32.250 --> 05:33.865
YOU KNOW THAT.

05:37.710 --> 05:39.109
[ FOLDER OPENS ]

05:39.120 --> 05:41.918
"19, AFRICAN-AMERICAN,
SHORT HAIR.

05:41.920 --> 05:43.547
DEFENSIVE WOUNDS
ON HIS HANDS AND FACE.

05:43.550 --> 05:44.869
PROLONGED ATTACKS."

05:47.090 --> 05:48.330
"FOUR CAVITIES."

05:48.340 --> 05:51.013
IT'S NOT HIM.
CHARLIE DIDN'T HAVE CAVITIES.

05:51.020 --> 05:52.009
AND STOP LOOKING.

05:55.890 --> 05:57.767
I TRUST YOU ALL HAD
A GOOD WORKOUT.

05:57.770 --> 05:59.476
WHOO-HOO!
YEAH!

05:59.480 --> 06:01.186
GOOD.

06:01.190 --> 06:03.101
BECAUSE BEFORE YOU GO HOME
FOR YOUR THREE-DAY WEEKEND,

06:03.110 --> 06:04.680
WE'RE GIVING YOU SOME HOMEWORK.

06:04.690 --> 06:05.896
[ TRAINEES GROAN ]
WHAT?!

06:05.900 --> 06:07.936
WHEN YOU ARE AN AGENT,

06:07.940 --> 06:09.783
WORK WILL ALWAYS BE
ON YOUR MIND.

06:09.790 --> 06:12.247
VICTIMS WILL HAUNT YOU,
EVIDENCE WILL ELUDE YOU,

06:12.250 --> 06:14.150
CASES WILL STAY WITH YOU --

06:14.160 --> 06:17.539
PARTICULARLY THOSE
THAT YOU FAIL TO SOLVE.

06:17.540 --> 06:20.202
IN LOCAL LAW ENFORCEMENT,
THEY'RE CALLED COLD CASES --

06:20.210 --> 06:21.620
ALL BUT CLOSED.

06:21.630 --> 06:24.838
BUT IN THE BUREAU,
WE DON'T BELIEVE IN COLD CASES.

06:24.840 --> 06:26.751
ALL OUR CASES REMAIN OPEN.

06:26.760 --> 06:30.844
THESE CASES ARE REFERRED TO
AS "PENDING INACTIVE."

06:30.850 --> 06:32.306
THE AGENCY LIKES TO CYCLE THEM

06:32.310 --> 06:34.210
THROUGH DIFFERENT AGENTS
OVER TIME,

06:34.220 --> 06:35.926
HOPING THAT SOMEONE
WILL FIND SOMETHING

06:35.930 --> 06:37.386
THAT SOMEONE ELSE MISSED.

06:37.390 --> 06:41.178
SO, YOUR GOAL WILL BE TO
LOOK THROUGH YOUR INACTIVE FILE

06:41.190 --> 06:42.817
AND FIND A NEW LEAD --

06:42.820 --> 06:44.811
SOMETHING THAT THE AGENTS
ON THE CASE DIDN'T THINK OF.

06:44.820 --> 06:47.015
NOW, IF THIS SEEMS
ALL BUT IMPOSSIBLE,

06:47.020 --> 06:48.976
THAT'S BECAUSE IT IS.

06:48.980 --> 06:51.653
BUT WHO KNOWS? MAYBE ONE OF YOU
WILL SURPRISE US.

06:51.660 --> 06:53.787
GOOD LUCK.
AND HAPPY NEW YEAR.

06:53.790 --> 06:56.327
[ APPLAUSE ]

07:01.420 --> 07:04.332
Vasquez: [Off-key]
O HOLY NIGHT
[ SHOWER WATER RUNNING ]

07:04.340 --> 07:08.663
THE STARS
ARE BRIGHTLY SHINING

07:08.670 --> 07:10.843
IT IS THE NIGHT

07:10.850 --> 07:14.217
OF OUR DEAR SAVIOR'S BIRTH
[ WATER STOPS ]

07:14.220 --> 07:16.757
FALL ON YOUR KNEES --

07:17.760 --> 07:19.762
AMAZING VOICE.

07:19.770 --> 07:21.146
BUT I THOUGHT
YOU WERE LEAVING.

07:21.150 --> 07:22.139
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:22.150 --> 07:23.014
ALEX.

07:24.230 --> 07:25.015
SHELBY?

07:25.730 --> 07:27.891
NIMAH?
HEY.

07:27.900 --> 07:30.733
WAIT, YOU GUYS -- DID WE ALL
JUST LIE ABOUT LEAVING?

07:30.740 --> 07:31.900
ARE YOU NOT
SEEING YOUR MOM?

07:31.910 --> 07:33.980
WHAT, AND SPEND NEW YEAR'S
GETTING REAMED OUT

07:33.990 --> 07:35.321
AND OPENING UP
OLD WOUNDS?

07:35.330 --> 07:36.319
NO, THAN KS.

07:36.330 --> 07:37.979
WHAT ABOUT
YOUR SORORITY SISTERS?

07:37.990 --> 07:40.038
UGH. THEY'RE EXACTLY
LIKE YOU THINK THEY ARE.

07:40.040 --> 07:41.667
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE SEEING RENATA.

07:41.670 --> 07:43.069
MY EX FOUND OUT
I WAS COMING,

07:43.080 --> 07:44.911
AND HE TOOK HER ON VACATION
TO DISNEY WORLD.

07:44.920 --> 07:46.956
GOING BACK TO DEARBORN AND
GETTING STUCK IN THE KITCHEN,

07:46.960 --> 07:48.166
HELPING MOM AND RAINA,

07:48.170 --> 07:50.047
COOKING FOR THE MEN
THE WHOLE WEEKEND?

07:50.050 --> 07:51.347
THAT'S NEVER HAPPENING
AGAIN.

07:51.350 --> 07:53.966
SO...
WE'RE THE ONLY ONES HERE?

07:53.970 --> 07:55.506
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THIS MEANS?

07:55.510 --> 07:56.920
SOMEONE'S GONNA MAKE
A LIQUOR RUN?

07:56.930 --> 07:58.466
NO.

07:58.470 --> 08:00.518
WE GET TO SOLVE
THE HARDEST CASES

08:00.520 --> 08:02.681
THE FBI's EVER HAD.

08:04.190 --> 08:06.090
Elias: PLEASE.
YOU HAVE TO LET ME THROUGH.

08:06.100 --> 08:07.852
I'M --
I'M ALEX PARRISH'S LAWYER.

08:07.860 --> 08:09.179
IT'S AN EMERGENCY!

08:09.190 --> 08:11.317
AGENT SHAW!
AGENT O'CONNOR!

08:11.320 --> 08:13.652
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?
ELIAS?

08:13.660 --> 08:15.196
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

08:15.200 --> 08:17.566
WHEN I WENT HOME LAST NIGHT,
I HAD THIS CRAZY FEELING,

08:17.570 --> 08:19.879
LIKE SOMEONE WAS WAITING FOR ME
INSIDE MY APARTMENT.

08:19.880 --> 08:21.825
I WAS SO SPOOKED,
I SLEPT IN MY OFFICE.

08:21.830 --> 08:24.207
AGENT HAYES CAN CORROBORATE.
HE WAS ON MY TAIL.

08:24.210 --> 08:25.950
BUT WHEN I LEI-T THERE
THIS MORNING,

08:25.960 --> 08:28.076
SOMEONE TRIED TO PUSH ME
INTO ONCOMING TRAFFIC.

08:28.080 --> 08:29.456
I DIDN'T SEE WHO IT WAS,

08:29.460 --> 08:32.964
BUT IF IT WASN'T FOR HAYES
PULLING ME UP, I MIGHT BE DEAD.

08:32.970 --> 08:35.882
I CAME STRAIGHT HERE.
I-I DON'T FEEL SAFE.

08:35.890 --> 08:37.619
DO YOU KNOW SOMETHING
I DON'T KNOW?

08:37.630 --> 08:39.086
IS THE REST OF THE CLASS
OKAY?

08:39.090 --> 08:42.093
YOU STILL HAVE YOUR TAILS
ON EVERYONE, RIGHT?

08:42.100 --> 08:44.011
BUT ALL THE TAILS
ARE ACCOUNTED FOR.

08:44.020 --> 08:45.180
THE ONLY ONE CALLED OFF
WAS SIMON.

08:45.190 --> 08:46.839
YOU TOLD THE AGENT
TO LEAVE.

08:46.850 --> 08:48.898
BECAUSE I DON'T THINK
SIMON'S PLAYING US.

08:48.900 --> 08:51.027
DITU REPORTS
NO CREDIT-CARD ACTIVITY

08:51.030 --> 08:52.941
NOR CCTV FOOTAGE
ON SIMON

08:52.950 --> 08:55.066
Al-TER HIS CONVERSATION
LAST NIGHT WITH ALEX.

08:55.070 --> 08:58.278
HE ONLY MADE ONE CALL --
TO OREN SHELEF.

08:58.280 --> 09:01.078
WHO WAS HIT BY A CAR NEAR
CLASSON TRIANGLE THIS MORNING.

09:01.080 --> 09:03.366
HIT BY A CAR --
LIKE WHAT ALMOST HAPPENED TO ME.

09:03.370 --> 09:04.496
CONVINCED YET?

09:04.500 --> 09:05.819
ALL RIGHT,
WE NEED TO GO TO SIMON'S HOUSE,

09:05.830 --> 09:07.411
SEE IF HE'S STILL THERE.

09:07.420 --> 09:08.910
EVERYONE THINKS I'M BEING
INTERVIEWED DOWN HERE, RIGHT?

09:08.920 --> 09:10.421
SO NO ONE'S
GONNA MISS ME.

09:10.430 --> 09:12.466
THERE'S A CAR OUTSIDE.
WE HAVE TO GO -- NOW.

09:12.470 --> 09:14.119
ALEX, YOU HAVE
THREE HOURS OF FREEDOM LEl-T.

09:14.130 --> 09:15.119
I HOPE IT'S ENOUGH.

09:26.520 --> 09:27.930
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

09:30.110 --> 09:31.145
CLEAR.

09:32.570 --> 09:33.946
OH, GOD.

09:33.950 --> 09:35.565
WHAT HAS HE DONE?

09:35.570 --> 09:37.185
WE DON'T KNOW THAT
FOR SURE.

09:37.190 --> 09:38.851
THIS LOOKS EXACTLY
LIKE HOW MY APARTMENT WAS FOUND.

09:38.860 --> 09:40.191
IT COULD BE STAGED.

09:40.200 --> 09:41.326
OR SIMON STAGED
YOUR APARTMENT.

09:41.330 --> 09:42.570
HIS COMPUTER
IS HERE.

09:42.580 --> 09:44.821
3D PRINTER.

09:44.830 --> 09:48.118
MAYBE HE...USED IT TO CONSTRUCT
SOME COMPONENT HE NEEDED.

09:48.120 --> 09:50.042
WHY SPECULATE
WHEN WE CAN FIND OUT?

09:51.710 --> 09:54.042
A HOTEL KEY CARD.
HOW IS THAT A PART OF A BOMB?

09:54.050 --> 09:55.506
IT'S NOT.
IT'S THE TARGET.

09:57.630 --> 09:59.257
THESE ARE BLUEPRINTS...

09:59.260 --> 10:01.137
AND A LIST OF ROOMS
ON HOLD

10:01.140 --> 10:03.631
FOR DONORS THIS WEEKEND
AT THE STEINER.

10:03.640 --> 10:05.631
THE SITE
FOR THE DONOR DINNER.

10:05.640 --> 10:06.675
LET'S GO!

10:08.220 --> 10:10.563
GOOD NEWS --
I FOUND BRANDON'S SNACKS.

10:10.570 --> 10:13.027
BAD NEWS -- THEY WERE
NEXT TO THE MOISTURIZER.

10:13.030 --> 10:15.601
NELSON HAS 42 PACKS
OF UNOPENED POKMON CARDS

10:15.610 --> 10:16.850
IN HIS CLOSET.

10:16.860 --> 10:17.929
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S WEIRDER --

10:17.940 --> 10:19.658
WHY HE HAS THEM
OR WHY HE HID THEM.

10:19.660 --> 10:21.036
MY SISTER
CAN'T GO TO SLEEP

10:21.040 --> 10:22.826
WITHOUT HAVING A STASH
OF AMAR ADDINE NEARBY.

10:22.830 --> 10:24.070
IF YOU PUT IT
IN YOUR CHEAP WINE,

10:24.080 --> 10:25.729
IT WILL TASTE
LIKE SANGRIA.

10:25.740 --> 10:27.071
HMM.

10:27.080 --> 10:29.071
ALEX?
DID YOU FIND ANYTHING?

10:30.510 --> 10:31.829
JUST REGRET.

10:31.840 --> 10:34.877
BACK HOME I GO

10:34.880 --> 10:38.372
TO THOSE I KNOW

10:38.380 --> 10:40.211
Nimah: WHY DID WE
HAVE TO DRINK FIRST?

10:40.220 --> 10:41.847
TO WARM UP.

10:44.680 --> 10:46.511
I AM WARM NOW.

10:46.520 --> 10:48.169
DID I MAKE A MISTAKE

10:48.180 --> 10:50.819
NOT SPENDING THE HOLIDAYS
WITH SOMEONE THAT I --

10:50.820 --> 10:52.526
SOMEONE THAT YOU WHAT?

10:52.530 --> 10:54.145
[ GASPS ]
NO, NO, NO, NO. WAIT.

10:54.150 --> 10:56.106
WHAT WERE YOU GONNA SAY?
IS IT FINALLY TIME?

10:56.110 --> 10:57.725
IS SHE GONNA SAY IT?
SAY WHAT?

10:57.730 --> 10:59.470
THE THING
YOU DIDN'T SAY TO RYAN?

10:59.480 --> 11:01.539
[ LOCK CLICKS, DOOR OPENS ]

11:01.540 --> 11:02.859
I GOT IT.

11:02.870 --> 11:04.986
NOW WE CAN STEAM.

11:04.990 --> 11:07.902
THIS VERMEER VANISHED FROM THE
GARDNER MUSEUM INTO THIN AIR.

11:07.910 --> 11:09.195
FORGET "PENDING INACTIVE.â€˜l

11:09.200 --> 11:10.747
THEY SHOULD CALL THESE
"PENDING IMPOSSIBLE."

11:10.750 --> 11:13.628
EACH IDEA I HAVE HAS ALREADY
BEEN THOUGHT OF AND DISMISSED

11:13.630 --> 11:16.121
BY EVERY NAT AND AGENT
ASSIGNED TO THIS CASE.

11:16.130 --> 11:18.280
NUH-UNH!
DO NOT OPEN THAT CASE AGAIN.

11:18.290 --> 11:19.757
MM!
SHE'S DRUNK-DIALING
RYAN.

11:19.760 --> 11:22.388
RE-DIALING RYAN.

11:22.390 --> 11:24.176
THE LAST TIME,
HE DIDN'T ANSWER MY PHONE.

11:24.180 --> 11:27.297
BECAUSE HE'S DOING WHAT
YOU ASKED! HE'S STAYING AWAY!

11:27.300 --> 11:28.790
DON'T OBSESS!

11:28.800 --> 11:30.973
COMING FROM THE GIRL
WHO HASN'T STOPPED REFRESHING

11:30.980 --> 11:32.857
HER BOYFRIEND'S
INSTAGRAM PICTURES FOR --

11:32.860 --> 11:34.896
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
DOWNLOADING EX SHIELD.

11:34.900 --> 11:37.562
IT'S AN APP THAT BLOCKS
YOUR NUMBER FOR OUTGOING CALLS.

11:37.570 --> 11:41.119
IT'S HOW I GET MY EX TO PICK UP
SO I CAN CHECK ON RENATA.

11:41.120 --> 11:42.405
WELCOME TO
THE let CENTURY.

11:42.410 --> 11:44.401
CALL
YOUR PENDING INACTIVE.

11:46.450 --> 11:48.236
UH...
I'M JUST GONNA DO IT.

11:48.240 --> 11:49.787
I'M -- I'M GONNA DO IT.

11:49.790 --> 11:51.701
BUT SPEAKER.
SPEAKER.

11:51.710 --> 11:53.166
[ Ringing ]
OKAY.

11:54.880 --> 11:56.950
RYAN: Hello?

11:56.960 --> 11:58.370
Hello?
Stop!

11:58.380 --> 12:00.211
WOMAN:
Ryan? Is everything okay?

12:00.220 --> 12:01.289
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
Hello?

12:03.600 --> 12:04.589
I NEED A DRINK.

12:07.100 --> 12:09.807
WELL...
WE'RE OUT OF WINE,

12:09.810 --> 12:12.347
AND POSTMATES WON'T
DELIVER HERE. I'VE CHECKED.

12:12.350 --> 12:14.102
SO...MAYBE COFFEE?

12:14.110 --> 12:16.010
THE CAFETERIA'S
CLOSED.

12:16.020 --> 12:17.726
I KNOW WHERE SOME IS.

12:19.190 --> 12:20.908
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

12:27.990 --> 12:29.867
I WAS GOING TO STEAL
YOUR COFFEE.

12:29.870 --> 12:31.576
GO AHEAD.

12:31.580 --> 12:34.572
JUST LEAVE ME ENOUGH
TO SPIKE MY WHISKEY WITH.

12:34.580 --> 12:36.707
IT MUST BE
A TERRIBLE TIME FOR YOU,

12:36.710 --> 12:38.325
WITH CHARLIE
STILL MISSING.

12:38.330 --> 12:39.797
CHARLIE'S NOT MISSING.

12:39.800 --> 12:42.371
CHARLIE IS EXACTLY
WHERE HE WANTS TO BE.

12:42.380 --> 12:44.962
BUT I THOUGHT THE EVIDENCE
POINTED TO A KIDNAPPING.

12:44.970 --> 12:47.040
ONLY BECAUSE I'M THE ONLY ONE
READY TO ACCEPT

12:47.050 --> 12:49.041
THAT HE IS THE MONSTER
IN THIS NIGHTMARE.

12:49.050 --> 12:50.938
OR PERHAPS
YOU DON'T WANT TO THINK OF HIM

12:50.940 --> 12:52.259
SUFFERING SOMEWHERE

12:52.270 --> 12:53.976
AND IT'S EASIER
TO MAKE HIM A MONSTER?

12:56.560 --> 12:59.267
WHY ARE YOU STILL HERE,
TRAINEE AMIN?

12:59.270 --> 13:01.238
I DON'T WANT TO GO
TO DEARBORN.

13:01.240 --> 13:03.390
IT HASN'T FELT LIKE HOME
FOR A LONG TIME.

13:03.400 --> 13:05.777
AND I SEE YOU DON'T WANT
TO GO HOME, EITHER.

13:09.360 --> 13:11.669
I MIGHT STAY FOR A DRINK
IF YOU INSIST.

13:13.040 --> 13:15.611
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

13:15.620 --> 13:18.783
UGH. IT'S NIMAH.
SHE'S IN MIRANDA'S OFFICE.

13:18.790 --> 13:21.042
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHO THAT WAS WITH RYAN.

13:21.050 --> 13:22.540
HE'S IN L.A., RIGHT?
YEAH.

13:22.550 --> 13:24.461
DOESN'T HE HAVE, LIKE,
THREE SISTERS THERE?

13:24.470 --> 13:26.711
GUYS, THAT DID NOT SOUND LIKE
A SISTER.

13:26.720 --> 13:27.914
ALL RIGHT, GET UP.

13:27.920 --> 13:29.410
GET UP.
COME ON.

13:29.420 --> 13:30.842
VASQUEZ.

13:30.850 --> 13:32.636
EVERYONE STAND
ON ONE FOOT.

13:32.640 --> 13:34.881
WHAT?
[ CHUCKLES ]
JUST DO IT.

13:34.890 --> 13:36.187
[ LAUGHS ]
COME ON.

13:36.190 --> 13:38.340
WHOEVER'S THE MOST SOBER
IS GONNA GET IN THEIR CAR,

13:38.350 --> 13:39.988
DRIVE US
TO THE OLD SETTLER,

13:39.990 --> 13:43.391
WHERE WHATEVER
D.E.A. TRAINEE OR MARINE

13:43.400 --> 13:45.732
WHO WANTS TO BUY
OUR MIDNIGHT KISSES CAN DO SO

13:45.740 --> 13:47.276
FOR THE PRICE OF CHEAP DRINKS
AND GOOD CONVERSATION.

13:47.280 --> 13:48.690
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

13:48.700 --> 13:50.998
MAYBE NOT EVEN
GOOD CONVERSATION.

13:51.000 --> 13:52.399
[ LAUGHTER ]

13:52.410 --> 13:53.536
WHOOP! CALEB!

13:53.540 --> 13:56.077
DON'T WORRY. I'M NOT
"MAGIC MIKE"-ING YOU.

13:56.080 --> 13:57.570
NICE.

13:57.580 --> 13:59.616
WHEN I GOT HOME,
INSTEAD OF THE NORMAL, INTIMATE

13:59.620 --> 14:01.417
HAAS FAMILY
HOLIDAY BLOODLETTING,

14:01.420 --> 14:03.411
THERE WERE 200 PEOPLE
AT MY HOUSE

14:03.420 --> 14:05.797
AND A TUX LAID OUT
ON MY BED.

14:05.800 --> 14:07.256
I PANICKED AND I FLED.

14:07.260 --> 14:09.455
BUT YOU STILL
PUT THE TUX ON.

14:09.460 --> 14:10.677
YEAH.

14:10.680 --> 14:12.261
DO YOU SEE THIS?

14:12.270 --> 14:14.170
I CAN'T GO BACK THERE
ALONE.

14:14.180 --> 14:15.511
I GET THAT YOU DON'T WANT
TO BE AROUND

14:15.520 --> 14:17.761
SOMEONE'S HAPPY FAMILY
RIGHT NOW, BUT I SWEAR TO YOU,

14:17.770 --> 14:19.010
THERE'S NOTHING FAMILIAL
ABOUT IT,

14:19.020 --> 14:20.601
AND NO ONE'S
GONNA BE HAPPY.

14:20.610 --> 14:23.773
EXCEPT FOR ME
IF I HAVE YOU BY MY SIDE.

14:23.780 --> 14:24.735
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

14:26.400 --> 14:27.606
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

14:27.610 --> 14:29.680
I'LL ONLY GO
IF THEY CAN COME, TOO.

14:35.790 --> 14:38.031
SIMON WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN ABLE
TO MAGNETIZE HIS KEY AT HOME.

14:38.040 --> 14:39.530
19 PEOPLE ASKED
FOR THEIR KEY CARDS

14:39.540 --> 14:41.792
TO BE RECODED
WITHIN THE PAST 12 HOURS.

14:41.800 --> 14:44.166
NINE OF THESE WERE ON THE LIST
OF DONOR ROOMS AT SIMON'S.

14:44.170 --> 14:46.047
DIVIDE AND CONQUER.

14:46.050 --> 14:47.290
STAY ON COMMS.

14:49.500 --> 14:50.671
FBI!

14:50.680 --> 14:51.419
CLEAR.

14:51.430 --> 14:52.761
FBI!

14:54.720 --> 14:55.800
CLEAR.

14:55.810 --> 14:57.710
FBI!

14:57.720 --> 14:58.926
SIMON!

14:58.930 --> 15:00.568
I DON'T KNOW IF THIS THING
IS REMOTE-CONTROLLED

15:00.570 --> 15:02.014
OR MOVEMENT-CONTROLLED.

15:02.020 --> 15:03.817
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

15:03.820 --> 15:05.685
I JUST KNOW
I WOKE UP WITH IT IN MY HANDS.

15:05.690 --> 15:07.601
BUT I'M PRETTY SURE IF I TAKE
MY FINGERS OFF THIS TRIGGER,

15:07.610 --> 15:09.566
THIS WHOLE BUILDING'S
GONNA BLOW.

15:12.490 --> 15:14.321
Nimah: ALEX!
OVER HERE!

15:14.790 --> 15:15.939
CAREFUL.

15:17.330 --> 15:19.787
THE LAST THING I REMEMBER
IS WALKING INTO MY HOUSE

15:19.790 --> 15:21.371
AND SOMEONE GRABBED ME.

15:21.380 --> 15:23.166
WHEN I WOKE UP, THIS THING
WAS TAPED TO MY HANDS.

15:23.170 --> 15:24.910
BUT I'M SWEATING SO MUCH

15:24.920 --> 15:26.205
THAT THE TAPE'S STARTING
TO GET LOOSE,

15:26.210 --> 15:27.996
OKAY.
AND I'M AFRAID
MY FINGER'S GONNA SLIP.

15:28.000 --> 15:30.093
YOU'RE OKAY.
I NEED YOU TO HELP ME.

15:30.100 --> 15:32.466
WE SAW YOUR WORKSHOP --
THE BLUEPRINTS, THE KEY CARD.

15:32.470 --> 15:34.097
SOMEBODY'S FRAMING ME.

15:34.100 --> 15:35.636
ALL RIGHT?
JUST LIKE THEY FRAMED ALEX.

15:35.640 --> 15:38.006
LOOK, FIND OREN.
HE CAN TELL YOU IT WASN'T ME.

15:38.010 --> 15:39.136
Alex: SIMON --
HE CAN TELL YOU!
JUST FIND OREN!

15:39.140 --> 15:41.051
SIMON --
Elias: SIMON, STOP.

15:41.060 --> 15:43.392
YOU CAME TO ME YESTERDAY,
ASKING ME TO REPRESENT YOU

15:43.400 --> 15:45.106
SO YOU'D HAVE
ATTORNEY/CLIENT PRIVILEGE.

15:45.110 --> 15:46.680
YOU ASKED ME
ABOUT EXTRADITION LAWS,

15:46.690 --> 15:47.725
ABOUT FLIGHT MANIFESTS.

15:47.730 --> 15:49.550
YOU WERE TVCOJNG TO RUN.

15:49.560 --> 15:50.868
I WANTED TO MAKE SURE
I WASN'T GONNA SPEND

15:50.870 --> 15:53.407
THE REST OF MY LIFE IN PRISON
FOR MY STOLEN PLANS.

15:53.410 --> 15:56.197
I DIDN'T HIDE ANYTHING
FROM YOU -- ANY OF YOU.

15:56.200 --> 15:59.067
LOOK --
EVIDENCE FOUND AT MY HOUSE,

15:59.070 --> 16:00.378
ME DRUGGED
AND BROUGHT TO A HOTEL --

16:00.380 --> 16:02.245
IS ANY OF THAT
GIVING YOU DJ VU?

16:02.250 --> 16:04.536
LET'S NOT WASTE
ANY MORE TIME, OKAY?

16:04.540 --> 16:07.498
JUST TELL US
WHERE THE BOMB IS -- PLEASE.

16:07.500 --> 16:10.173
THINK OF
WHO COULD HAVE DONE THIS.

16:10.180 --> 16:12.501
THEY ARE THE ONLY PERSON
WHO CAN ANSWER THAT QUESTION.

16:12.510 --> 16:14.842
YOU GOT TO BELIEVE ME.

16:17.890 --> 16:20.222
YOU GREW UP HERE?
ARE YOU KIDDING?

16:20.230 --> 16:22.972
MY MOM WAITED TO BUY HOGWARTS
UNTIL AFTER MY SISTER AND I LEl-T

16:22.980 --> 16:25.187
SO WE WOULD LEARN
HUMILITY AND VALUES.

16:25.190 --> 16:26.225
WHERE IS YOUR MOTHER?

16:26.230 --> 16:28.221
I'D LIKE TO THANK HER
FOR TRYING.

16:28.230 --> 16:30.107
AND I CAN'T WAIT
TO SEE THE LOOK ON HER FACE

16:30.110 --> 16:31.987
WHEN I FINALLY INTRODUCE HER
TO SOMEBODY OLD ENOUGH TO VOTE.

16:31.990 --> 16:32.945
[ LAUGHS ]

16:32.950 --> 16:34.065
GUESS
I'M GETTING COATS?

16:34.070 --> 16:35.731
I'LL GET DRINKS.
OKAY.

16:35.740 --> 16:37.230
DON'T THINK
I HAVE THE ENERGY

16:37.240 --> 16:39.196
TO ADD
TO MY ALREADY MAD RUSH

16:39.200 --> 16:40.371
JUST 'CAUSE
IT'S 'TIS THE SEASON

16:40.380 --> 16:42.371
IT'S, UH, DOWN THE HALL,
TO THE LEI-T, AND --

16:42.380 --> 16:43.495
I'LL JUST -- I'LL SHOW YOU.
COME ON.

16:43.500 --> 16:45.115
OH, THANK YOU.

16:45.120 --> 16:47.827
I'VE BEEN TO MY FAIR SHARE
OF SOIRES AT THE HAAS COMPOUND.

16:47.830 --> 16:49.741
I'VE NEVER EVEN BEEN IN A HOUSE
BIG ENOUGH TO GET LOST IN.

16:49.750 --> 16:51.422
ARE YOU A POLITICIAN?

16:51.430 --> 16:52.624
OH,
IT'S REALLY NOT NICE

16:52.630 --> 16:54.507
TO INSULT SOMEONE
THAT YOU'VE JUST MET.

16:54.510 --> 16:56.296
HANNAH WYLAND --
JOINT TERRORISM.

16:56.300 --> 16:58.086
AS IN MY DREAM JOB!

16:58.090 --> 17:00.342
ALEXANDER PARRISH --
MERE TRAINEE.

17:00.350 --> 17:02.056
THEY LET YOU GUYS OUT
FOR NEW YEAR'S?

17:02.060 --> 17:03.800
YEAH.
I HAD A FEVER OF 104,

17:03.810 --> 17:05.346
AND THEY STILL MADE ME DO
THE STEEPLECHASE.

17:05.350 --> 17:06.396
MY GOD.

17:06.400 --> 17:08.129
IF IT WASN'T
AN OPEN BAR ALREADY,

17:08.140 --> 17:10.062
I WOULD TOTALLY ASK
TO BUY YOU A DRINK.

17:10.070 --> 17:11.947
AND I WOULD SAY,
"YES, PLEASE, AND RIGHT AWAY,"

17:11.950 --> 17:14.066
BUT I PROMISED MY GUY
THAT I'D MEET HIM AT THE DOOR.

17:14.070 --> 17:16.607
HE'S A GOOD ONE,
BUT HE HATES A PARTY.

17:16.610 --> 17:17.941
USUALLY, I CAN'T FEEL MY HAND
AN HOUR IN

17:17.950 --> 17:19.144
FROM HIM SQUEEZING IT
SO HARD.

17:19.150 --> 17:20.822
WOW.

17:20.830 --> 17:22.991
DREAM JOB
AND DREAM HUSBAND.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.412
I THOUGHT THOSE TWO
WERE MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE.

17:25.420 --> 17:27.035
NO. THAT'S JUST THE MEDIA
TRYING TO HOLD US BACK.

17:27.040 --> 17:28.280
[ CHUCKLES ]
SO, I'LL SEE YOU
IN THERE?

17:28.290 --> 17:29.109
YEAH.
OKAY.

17:31.260 --> 17:33.296
HEY, MOM.

17:33.300 --> 17:34.665
I WANT TO
INTRODUCE YOU TO...

17:34.670 --> 17:36.160
SHELBY WYATT!

17:36.170 --> 17:37.876
SENATOR HAAS,
IT IS AN HONOR.

17:37.880 --> 17:39.928
MY HUSBAND'S TOLD ME
ABOUT YOU.

17:39.930 --> 17:42.091
I DIDN'T REALIZE
YOU GUYS WERE ON SPEAKING TERMS.

17:42.100 --> 17:43.556
TOP OF YOUR CLASS
AT QUANTICO --

17:43.560 --> 17:45.846
Al-TER REBUILDING
YOUR FAMILY'S BUSINESS, NO LESS.

17:45.850 --> 17:47.431
QUITE A FEAT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:47.440 --> 17:49.476
YOUR PARENTS WOULD BE
VERY PROUD.

17:49.480 --> 17:51.528
I MET THEM A FEW TIMES.

17:51.530 --> 17:53.896
I AM SO SORRY
FOR WHAT HAPPENED.

17:53.900 --> 17:56.778
WE LOST TOO MUCH THAT DAY --
EACH AND EVERY ONE OF US.

17:56.780 --> 17:58.736
OH, YOU WERE THERE.

17:58.740 --> 18:01.152
I REMEMBER THE PHOTO
IN ALL THE PAPERS.

18:01.160 --> 18:04.118
YOU, AN AGENT, WALKED
RIGHT INTO THAT SECOND TOWER

18:04.120 --> 18:05.576
WHEN EVERYONE ELSE
WAS RUNNING THE OTHER WAY.

18:05.580 --> 18:07.036
YEAH, THAT PHOTO
GOT HER ELECTED.

18:07.040 --> 18:08.075
CALEB!

18:08.080 --> 18:09.490
[ Chuckling ] WHAT?

18:09.500 --> 18:11.001
I'M PROUD OF MY MOM.

18:11.010 --> 18:13.080
MY SON SEES EVERYTHING I DO
AS POLITICAL --

18:13.090 --> 18:14.580
EVEN RAISING HIM.

18:14.590 --> 18:17.582
BUT I WOULD HAVE GIVEN IT ALL UP
IF HE'D ASKED ME TO.

18:17.590 --> 18:19.126
WHERE'S YOUR FATHER?

18:19.130 --> 18:21.212
I PROMISED I'D INTRODUCE HIM
TO BEN CARSON.

18:21.220 --> 18:23.131
GOD KNOWS WHY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:23.140 --> 18:25.017
I LOOK FORWARD
TO SPEAKING TO YOU AGAIN SOON.

18:25.020 --> 18:26.089
EXCUSE ME.

18:28.810 --> 18:31.688
WHAT'S WRONG?
THE GREAT CLAIRE HAAS APPROVED.

18:31.690 --> 18:34.989
I BASICALLY JUST GOT YOU
THE IRON THRONE.

18:34.990 --> 18:36.719
MY DAD DOESN'T EVEN LIVE
IN THIS HOUSE.

18:36.730 --> 18:40.279
MY PARENTS -- THEY DON'T TALK
TO EACH OTHER ON PRINCIPLE.

18:40.290 --> 18:42.576
SOMETHING'S GOING ON.

18:42.580 --> 18:45.401
EVERY YEAR, MIRANDA SENDS
SOME NAT TO TALK TO ME

18:45.410 --> 18:47.321
ABOUT THAT DAMN
VERMEER THEl-T.

18:47.330 --> 18:49.400
USUALLY,
THEY COME TO MY OFFICE.

18:49.410 --> 18:51.878
ONE GUY CAUGHT ME
AT TRADER JOE'S.

18:51.880 --> 18:54.952
BUT YOU'RE THE FIRST TO
ACCOST ME AT A COCKTAIL PARTY.

18:54.960 --> 18:57.542
IF YOU COULD JUST WALK ME
THROUGH THE DETAILS -- HELP ME.

18:57.550 --> 19:00.178
SOM ETIM ES,
THINGS JUST DISAPPEAR.

19:00.180 --> 19:03.252
LIKE I AM --
FROM THIS CONVERSATION.

19:03.260 --> 19:06.593
I AM GONNA GO GET MYSELF
THAT MARTINI I EARNED.

19:06.600 --> 19:09.091
ALL RIGHT, WELL, I'LL WAIT
OVER HERE, WHERE IT'S SAFE.

19:10.190 --> 19:11.600
CALEB.

19:11.610 --> 19:13.066
OR NOT.

19:13.070 --> 19:14.719
I HAVE BEEN HEARING
GREAT THINGS

19:14.730 --> 19:16.436
ABOUT YOUR TRAINING
AT QUANTICO.

19:18.360 --> 19:19.850
YOUR MOTHER SAID
I WAS WRONG TO DOUBT YOU.

19:19.860 --> 19:21.487
I'M BEGINNING TO BELIEVE
SHE'S RIGHT.

19:21.490 --> 19:23.276
WELL, YOU AND MOM
AGREEING ABOUT ANYTHING

19:23.280 --> 19:25.532
IS THREAT LEVEL BRAVO,
SO WHAT GIVES?

19:25.540 --> 19:27.360
NOTHING GIVES.
WE'VE --

19:27.370 --> 19:30.669
WE'VE JUST BEEN TALKING A LOT
ABOUT YOU LATELY.

19:30.670 --> 19:32.581
WE'RE TALKING A LOT,
ACTUALLY.

19:32.590 --> 19:34.626
WHAT, ARE YOU GUYS
GETTING BACK TOGETHER?

19:34.630 --> 19:36.871
WELL, SHE HAS SAID SHE WANTS
TO GIVE IT ANOTHER SHOT.

19:38.250 --> 19:39.285
THOUGHT YOU'D BE HAPPY.

19:39.290 --> 19:40.712
IAM.

19:45.140 --> 19:48.883
THIS HOLIDAY IS WAY WORSE
THAN VALENTINE'S DAY.

19:48.890 --> 19:51.108
AT LEAST THEN, IF YOU'RE SINGLE,
YOU'RE NOT A COMPLETE FAILURE.

19:51.110 --> 19:53.852
BUT NO ONE TO KISS
ON NEW YEAR'S EVE -- EPIC FAIL.

19:53.860 --> 19:55.145
[ SIGHS ]

19:55.150 --> 19:56.765
STOP TORTURING YOURSELF.
I CAN'T.

19:56.770 --> 19:58.351
WELL,
THEN STOP TORTURING ME.

19:58.360 --> 19:59.258
CALL HIM AND TELL HIM
YOU MADE A MISTAKE.

19:59.270 --> 20:00.942
BUT IF HE'S WITH
SOMEONE ELSE, THERE'S --

20:00.950 --> 20:02.235
YOU JUST SAW HIM
TWO WEEKS AGO.

20:02.240 --> 20:03.309
HE DIDN'T MEET,
FALL IN LOVE WITH,

20:03.320 --> 20:04.867
AND MARRY A WOMAN
IN TWO WEEKS.

20:04.870 --> 20:06.110
NO MORE BLOCKING.

20:06.120 --> 20:07.985
CLICK THAT CONTACT.

20:10.250 --> 20:12.127
[ SIGHS ]

20:12.130 --> 20:13.586
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

20:13.590 --> 20:15.319
[ Ringing ]

20:15.330 --> 20:18.128
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

20:18.130 --> 20:20.382
[ Ringing continues ]

20:20.390 --> 20:22.836
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

20:22.840 --> 20:24.000
[ Ringing continues ]

20:24.010 --> 20:25.420
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

20:25.430 --> 20:26.419
[ RINGING STOPS ]

20:26.430 --> 20:27.670
ALEX?

20:31.350 --> 20:32.647
LOOK,
IF I WAS THE BOMBER,

20:32.650 --> 20:34.049
WOULDN'T I HAVE
GONE THROUGH WITH IT ALREADY?

20:34.060 --> 20:35.846
THE CONVENTION
ISN'T FOR HOURS.

20:35.850 --> 20:38.011
THE CONVENTION? WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH THIS?

20:38.020 --> 20:40.659
THE FACT THAT IT'S TODAY?
THE DINNER DOWNSTAIRS?

20:40.660 --> 20:42.651
HOW DID YOU FIND ME?

20:42.660 --> 20:44.730
YOU WERE THE ONLY ONE
WITHOUT A TAIL LAST NIGHT.

20:44.740 --> 20:46.025
YEAH.

20:46.030 --> 20:48.271
BUT HOW DID YOU KNOW
TO LOOK?

20:50.160 --> 20:51.627
HE'LL SAY ANYTHING
TO GET OUT OF THIS.

20:51.630 --> 20:53.245
WE CAUGHT YOU RED-HANDED.

20:53.250 --> 20:55.286
YOU LITERALLY HAVE YOUR FINGER
ON A TRIGGER RIGHT THIS SECOND.

20:55.290 --> 20:57.576
I DON'T KNOW
WHY YOU WOULD DO THIS,

20:57.580 --> 21:00.469
BUT I KNOW THAT YOU WOULD DO
ANYTHING TO SAVE YOUR OWN SKIN.

21:00.470 --> 21:02.631
JUST LIKE WHEN YOU RAN OUT
OF THAT TEST AT QUANTICO.

21:05.470 --> 21:06.539
ALEX.

21:08.760 --> 21:10.842
ARE YOU KIDDING ME
RIGHT NOW?

21:12.060 --> 21:14.472
IT'S SIMON.
IT HAS TO BE.

21:14.480 --> 21:15.845
NO.

21:15.850 --> 21:17.260
I HAVE ALWAYS
SEEN THROUGH YOUR LIES,

21:17.270 --> 21:18.680
BUT THIS TIME,
I'M NOT SURE.

21:18.690 --> 21:20.487
IF YOU REALLY BELIEVE IT'S ME
AND NOT HIM,

21:20.490 --> 21:23.061
THEN WHY DON'T I JUST
LET GO OF THIS TRIGGER?

21:23.070 --> 21:24.025
SIMON, DON'T!
WHY NOT?!

21:26.360 --> 21:28.351
IF I'M THE REAL TERRORIST,
WHAT AM I WAITING FOR?

21:28.360 --> 21:29.736
YOU WOULDN'T.

21:29.740 --> 21:31.071
YOU GOT
WHAT YOU WANTED --

21:31.080 --> 21:33.321
ALL THAT TIME AT QUANTICO,
PLAYING ME,

21:33.330 --> 21:35.161
SETTING ME UP.

21:35.170 --> 21:37.286
IT WASN'T ABOUT
MY SEXUALITY.

21:37.290 --> 21:38.496
YOU WERE JUST TRYING
TO GET CLOSE TO ME

21:38.500 --> 21:40.411
SO YOU COULD FIND OUT
MY WEAKNESSES --

21:40.420 --> 21:43.469
GET INSIDE MY HEAD
SO YOU COULD FRAME ME.

21:43.470 --> 21:45.620
WELL, IF THAT WAS YOUR PLAN,
IT WORKED.

21:45.630 --> 21:47.712
I GO DOWN
AS THE GRAND CENTRAL BOMBER,

21:47.720 --> 21:48.675
AND YOU WALK AWAY.

21:48.680 --> 21:50.807
YOU'RE INSANE.

21:50.810 --> 21:53.517
YOU EVER WANT TO PUSH A BUTTON
AND MAKE IT ALL GO AWAY?

21:53.520 --> 21:54.555
SIMON.

21:54.560 --> 21:57.347
EVERYONE YOU EVER LOVED
AND LOST,

21:57.350 --> 21:58.726
EVERYTHING
THAT EVER HURT YOU --

21:58.730 --> 22:01.392
JUST ONE BUTTON.

22:01.400 --> 22:03.356
NO MORE FIGHTING.

22:03.360 --> 22:04.850
NO MORE REGRETS.

22:04.860 --> 22:07.397
NO MORE NOISE.

22:07.400 --> 22:09.061
BLOW IT ALL UP
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

22:09.070 --> 22:10.617
SIMON!

22:10.620 --> 22:13.157
BLOW IT ALL UP JUST SO YOU CAN
GET SOME DAMN QUIET.

22:13.160 --> 22:14.320
SIMON!

22:14.330 --> 22:15.820
YOU WANTED THEM
TO FIND ME.

22:15.830 --> 22:18.071
THAT'S WHY YOU BROUGHT THEM HERE
BEFORE THIS BOMB WENT OFF.

22:18.080 --> 22:19.866
SO YOU BETTER START
TELLING THE TRUTH,

22:19.870 --> 22:23.124
OR IT IS GONNA GET
REAL, REAL QUIET.

22:25.010 --> 22:26.500
THREE...
SIMON!

22:26.510 --> 22:27.829
TWO...
Vasquez: MY GOD!

22:27.840 --> 22:29.296
SIMON!
ONE!

22:29.300 --> 22:31.882
STOP, STOP!
THEY'LL KILL ME!

22:31.890 --> 22:33.096
THEY'LL KILL ME.

22:36.810 --> 22:38.630
A WEEK AGO,
I GOT A CALL FROM SOMEONE.

22:38.640 --> 22:39.959
THEY DISGUISED
THEIR VOICE.

22:39.970 --> 22:43.679
WHOEVER IT WAS HAD PROOF
THAT I'D FALSIFIED EVIDENCE

22:43.690 --> 22:46.739
AS A TRIAL ATTORNEY
IN A FEW CAPITAL CASES.

22:46.740 --> 22:48.389
THEY SAID THEY'D MAKE SURE
I WENT TO JAIL

22:48.400 --> 22:51.073
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE
IF I DIDN'T DO WHAT I WAS TOLD.

22:51.080 --> 22:53.981
THEY KNEW I'D GONE TO QUANTICO
AND THAT I KNEW YOU, ALEX.

22:53.990 --> 22:56.618
YOU GRABBED ME
WHEN I WAS ON MY WAY TO WORK.

22:56.620 --> 22:59.657
YOU DRUGGED ME AND THEN TOOK ME
BACK TO GRAND CENTRAL,

22:59.660 --> 23:01.332
PUT ME ON THAT RUBBLE --

23:01.340 --> 23:03.706
THAT WASN'T ME.
I WAS GONE BY THEN.

23:03.710 --> 23:05.621
I NEVER THOUGHT
THE BOMB WAS REAL.

23:05.630 --> 23:08.997
I THOUGHT I WAS JUST
SETTING YOU UP FOR AN ATTEMPT.

23:09.000 --> 23:11.002
I SWEAR, I NEVER
WOULD HAVE DONE IT OTHERWISE.

23:11.010 --> 23:14.764
THE BLOOD OF 133 PEOPLE
IS ON YOUR HANDS, ELIAS.

23:14.770 --> 23:16.340
YOU THINK
I DON'T KNOW THAT?

23:16.350 --> 23:19.422
AFTER THE BOMB WENT OFF, I KNEW
IT WAS JUST A MATTER OF TIME

23:19.430 --> 23:21.682
BEFORE I WAS FOUND OUT,
AND I FELT HORRIBLE.

23:21.690 --> 23:23.351
ALEX CALLING YOU
TO REPRESENT HER

23:23.360 --> 23:24.975
MUST HAVE BEEN
A DREAM COME TRUE, HUH?

23:24.980 --> 23:26.641
ALL THAT ACCESS
WE GAVE YOU?

23:26.650 --> 23:28.106
YOU WERE
IN THE CENTER OF IT ALL.

23:28.110 --> 23:29.816
I THOUGHT THE WORST WAS OVER
UNTIL YESTERDAY,

23:29.820 --> 23:31.151
WHEN THE TERRORIST
CALLED ME AGAIN

23:31.160 --> 23:33.196
AND SAID
I HAD ONE LAST TASK.

23:33.200 --> 23:35.441
AND THEN
I'D BE FREE FOREVER.

23:35.450 --> 23:37.441
I WAS TO BRING THAT TRIGGER
TO THIS HOTEL

23:37.450 --> 23:38.690
AND WAIT
FOR INSTRUCTIONS.

23:38.700 --> 23:40.361
I PANICKED.

23:40.370 --> 23:42.702
I-I MEAN, I DIDN'T WANT TO BE
RESPONSIBLE FOR ANY MORE DEATHS.

23:42.710 --> 23:44.450
SO WHY NOT COME TO US?
WE COULD HAVE HELPED YOU.

23:44.460 --> 23:45.996
LIKE THE FBI HELPED YOU?

23:46.000 --> 23:47.160
TH EY'D ARREST ME.

23:47.170 --> 23:48.580
TERRORIST OR NOT,
I AM RESPONSIBLE.

23:48.590 --> 23:49.909
AND I THOUGHT
OF A BETTER WAY.

23:49.920 --> 23:51.421
YEAH,
DRUGGING AND FRAMING ME?

23:51.430 --> 23:53.671
SINCE YOU KNEW THE BOMBER
MODELED HIS STUFF
OFF OF MY WORK?

23:53.680 --> 23:55.921
AND GIVEN EVERYTHING
YOU'D DONE IN YOUR LIFE...

23:55.930 --> 23:58.000
INSTEAD OF TAKING RESPONSIBILITY
FOR YOURSELF,

23:58.010 --> 24:01.104
YOU DECIDED MY LIFE FOR YOURS
WAS A PRETTY FAIR TRADE.

24:01.110 --> 24:03.681
THE FBI HAD
ENOUGH CIRCUMSTANTIAL EVIDENCE.

24:03.690 --> 24:05.510
I JUST HAD TO POINT THEM
IN YOUR DIRECTION.

24:05.520 --> 24:07.932
SO I PRETENDED
TO SLEEP IN MY OFFICE,

24:07.940 --> 24:09.146
SLIPPED MY TAIL.

24:09.150 --> 24:10.265
YOU'RE DESPICABLE.

24:10.270 --> 24:12.329
I WANTED YOU
TO FIND SIMON.

24:12.330 --> 24:14.981
I BROUGHT YOU HERE
BECAUSE I WANT YOU TO
TRY AND STOP THIS BOMB.

24:14.990 --> 24:16.821
I HAD THREE CHOICES --
COME CLEAN,

24:16.830 --> 24:18.980
CARRY OUT
THE SECOND ATTACK MYSELF,

24:18.990 --> 24:21.038
OR FRAME SIMON
AND HOPE TO STOP IT.

24:21.040 --> 24:23.122
LOOK, THE ONLY THING
WE WANT TO HEAR FROM YOU

24:23.130 --> 24:24.620
IS WHERE THE BOMB IS.

24:24.630 --> 24:25.915
I DON'T KNOW.

24:25.920 --> 24:27.069
THE ONLY THING
THAT MAKES SENSE

24:27.080 --> 24:28.160
IS THAT IT'S IN THIS BUILDING
SOMEWHERE.

24:28.170 --> 24:30.240
THEY WANTED ME HERE,
AND THEY WANTED ME DEAD.

24:30.250 --> 24:32.582
PLEASE JUST DON'T LET GO
OF THAT TRIGGER, SIMON.

24:34.260 --> 24:35.796
CALL LIAM NOW.

24:37.140 --> 24:38.880
AND THEN VICE PRESIDENT BIDEN
IS GOING TO --

24:38.890 --> 24:40.767
EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.
WE ARE EVACUATING.

24:40.770 --> 24:43.091
WE HAVE A CREDIBLE THREAT, AND
WE NEED EVERYONE OUT RIGHT NOW.

24:43.100 --> 24:44.260
HOW CREDIBLE?

24:44.270 --> 24:46.306
THE BOMB SQUAD'S
BEEN ON THIS HOTEL FOR DAYS.

24:46.310 --> 24:47.766
TRUST ME --
THIS IS NOT A DRILL. OKAY?

24:47.770 --> 24:49.761
WE'RE MOVING EVERYONE
TO THE E.C.C.

24:49.770 --> 24:50.862
LET'S GO.

24:53.070 --> 24:54.867
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

24:57.530 --> 24:59.862
WHAT? YOUR WIFE LETS YOU GO INTO
BATHROOMS WITH EX-GIRLFRIENDS?

24:59.870 --> 25:01.167
SHE IS NOT MY WIFE.

25:01.170 --> 25:01.955
SHE'S NOT?

25:01.960 --> 25:02.779
SHE'S MY EX-WIFE.

25:04.170 --> 25:06.320
W-WE'RE UNDERCOVER.
OKAY?

25:06.330 --> 25:08.207
YOU'RE ALWAYS UNDERCOVER.

25:08.210 --> 25:09.416
WE'RE STILL FRIENDS.

25:09.420 --> 25:10.671
LOOK, IF YOU KNEW
THE WHOLE STORY,

25:10.680 --> 25:12.386
IT WOULDN'T EVEN BE AN ISSUE
WITH YOU RIGHT NOW.

25:12.390 --> 25:14.290
YOU DID NOT JUST SAY THAT
IF I KNOW THE WHOLE STORY --

25:14.300 --> 25:15.756
ALEX, LISTEN TO ME.

25:15.760 --> 25:18.172
EVERYONE AT H.Q. KNOWS
WE WORK WELL AS PARTNERS, OKAY?

25:18.180 --> 25:20.557
SO THEY ASSIGN US TO AN OP
WHERE WE'RE MARRIED.

25:20.560 --> 25:21.686
AND YOU TOLD ME
TO LEAVE.

25:21.690 --> 25:22.930
I NEVER TOLD YOU
TO LEAVE!

25:22.940 --> 25:24.680
WELL, YOU SURE AS HELL
DIDN'T ASK ME TO STAY.

25:26.020 --> 25:27.396
WELL, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE IN LOS ANGELES.

25:27.400 --> 25:29.800
IF I KNEW YOU WERE
30 MINUTES AWAY, I WOULD HAVE --

25:29.810 --> 25:31.698
YOU WOULD HAVE WHAT?

25:31.700 --> 25:33.691
THEN YOU WOULD HAVE
ASKED ME TO STAY?

25:33.700 --> 25:35.315
ALEX, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH ME

25:35.320 --> 25:36.639
WHEN I'M 2 FEET AWAY.

25:36.650 --> 25:38.732
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

25:42.290 --> 25:44.201
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

25:46.330 --> 25:47.649
I...

25:47.660 --> 25:49.366
I CAN'T BE HERE
RIGHT NOW.

25:49.370 --> 25:50.155
SORRY.

25:54.130 --> 25:56.712
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN HOME
SINCE THAT NIGHT, HAVE YOU?

25:56.720 --> 25:59.666
HE CAN'T GET TO ME HERE.

25:59.670 --> 26:02.468
YOU REMIND ME
OF MY AUNT.

26:02.480 --> 26:04.220
AFTER THE CIVIL WAR,
SHE WAS CONVINCED

26:04.230 --> 26:07.017
THAT THE LEBANESE FORCES
WERE TRYING TO KILL HER.

26:07.020 --> 26:09.011
EVERY SIREN SHE HEARD,

26:09.020 --> 26:11.602
EVERY FOOTSTEP WAS PROOF
SHE WAS BEING HUNTED.

26:11.610 --> 26:12.770
MAYBE SHE WAS.

26:12.780 --> 26:14.236
[ Scoffing ]
OF COURSE NOT.

26:14.240 --> 26:17.232
SHE JUST COULDN'T
GET OUT OF THIS FRAME OF MIND.

26:17.240 --> 26:19.982
JUST LIKE WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY PEOPLE Al-TER 9/11.

26:19.990 --> 26:23.448
EVERY ARAB MAN
WAS TARGETED, QUESTIONED,

26:23.460 --> 26:24.859
FOLLOWED, SURVEILLED.

26:24.870 --> 26:27.111
THEY SAW US
NOT AS HUMANS,

26:27.120 --> 26:31.830
BUT AS THIS HAND
OF A MONSTER THAT HATED AMERICA.

26:31.840 --> 26:34.832
I SAW PEOPLE IN MY COMMUNITY
ACT OUT

26:34.840 --> 26:36.876
IN WAYS
THEY NEVER WOULD HAVE

26:36.880 --> 26:39.417
IF THEY HADN'T BEEN TREATED
SO UNJUSTLY.

26:39.420 --> 26:41.888
WHATEVER YOU IMAGINE
PEOPLE MIGHT HAVE DONE,

26:41.890 --> 26:44.097
JUST DON'T LOSE FAITH
IN THEIR HUMANITY,

26:44.100 --> 26:45.670
BECAUSE WHEN YOU DO,

26:45.680 --> 26:47.671
THAT'S WHEN
YOU MAKE THE MONSTER.

26:49.310 --> 26:51.813
IS IT POSSIBLE YOU COULD BE
WRONG ABOUT CHARLIE?

26:54.860 --> 26:56.430
I KNOW WHO HE IS.

26:56.440 --> 26:59.648
AND MY WORST FEAR
IS THAT SOMEDAY,

26:59.650 --> 27:01.732
EVERYONE ELSE WILL, TOO.

27:01.740 --> 27:03.867
HAPPY NEW YEAR, NIMAH.

27:06.410 --> 27:07.866
HAPPY NEW YEAR.

27:07.870 --> 27:09.906
Claire:
PLEASE -- JOIN ME.

27:09.910 --> 27:12.083
I JUST NEEDED A MOMENT
TO MYSELF.

27:14.050 --> 27:15.870
DID YOU KNOW YOU WANTED
TO GO INTO POLITICS

27:15.880 --> 27:18.007
WHEN YOU WERE
AT THE FBI?

27:18.010 --> 27:20.581
I LIKE TO SAY THAT I WAS CALLED
TO PUBLIC SERVICE,

27:20.590 --> 27:21.807
BUT THAT'S NOT TRUE.

27:21.810 --> 27:23.801
I SAW
WHAT PASSED FOR LEADERSHIP --

27:23.810 --> 27:25.846
MEN TELLING PEOPLE
TO DO ONE THING

27:25.850 --> 27:27.465
WHILE THEY DO
THE OPPOSITE.

27:27.470 --> 27:29.711
WOMEN LEAD BY EXAMPLE.

27:29.720 --> 27:30.971
WE HAVE TO.

27:30.980 --> 27:33.437
THEY SHINE A BRIGHTER LIGHT
ON US.

27:33.440 --> 27:35.226
I KNOW THAT SOUNDS
LIKE A STUMP SPEECH.

27:35.230 --> 27:37.607
CALEB SAYS I'M ALWAYS
RUNNING FOR SOMETHING.

27:37.610 --> 27:38.429
BUT IT'S TRUE.

27:38.440 --> 27:40.067
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:40.070 --> 27:41.981
HE'S A GOOD SON.

27:41.990 --> 27:43.867
HE'LL BE A GOOD MAN,
I THINK.

27:45.160 --> 27:47.572
SHOULD I BE
AFRAID OF HIM?

27:47.580 --> 27:50.276
I REALLY LOVE HIM.

27:50.280 --> 27:53.499
BUT YOUR HUSBAND TOLD ME
SOME THINGS.

27:53.500 --> 27:56.628
YOU SHOULDN'T BE
AFRAID OF HIM.

27:56.630 --> 27:58.996
YOU SHOULD BE AFRAID
OF WHAT PEOPLE CAN DO TO HIM.

27:59.000 --> 28:01.389
MY SON HAS A...

28:01.390 --> 28:04.006
A GOOD HEART.

28:04.010 --> 28:06.387
THE KIND
PEOPLE TAKE ADVANTAGE OF.

28:06.390 --> 28:09.348
I'VE HAD TO DISTANCE MYSELF
FROM SOME THINGS THAT HE'S DONE,

28:09.350 --> 28:11.398
BUT ONLY BECAUSE I KNOW
THEY WEREN'T REALLY HIM.

28:11.400 --> 28:14.563
THEY WERE...PEOPLE USING HIM
TO GET AT US.

28:14.570 --> 28:17.141
THE CULT?

28:17.150 --> 28:20.938
IT CAUSED A LOT OF PAIN
FOR OUR FAMILY.

28:20.950 --> 28:23.191
CLAYTON AND I DISAGREED
OVER HOW TO HANDLE IT.

28:23.200 --> 28:25.316
HE WANTED TO CATCH THE CULT
RED-HANDED

28:25.320 --> 28:28.778
INSTEAD OF EXTRACTING CALEB
BEFORE IT WENT THAT FAR.

28:30.450 --> 28:32.998
HE MADE HIS CHOICE,
AND I HAD TO FOLLOW.

28:33.000 --> 28:35.582
IT COST
CALEB'S FAITH IN ME.

28:36.880 --> 28:39.417
AND MY FAITH
IN MY HUSBAND.

28:39.420 --> 28:41.593
UNTIL NOW.

28:41.600 --> 28:43.966
NOW WE'RE TRYING AGAIN.
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:43.970 --> 28:46.211
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
MY GOODNESS.

28:46.220 --> 28:48.597
YOU CAME OUT HERE
TO MAKE A GOOD IMPRESSION,

28:48.600 --> 28:51.478
AND I HAVE TURNED YOU
INTO MY THERAPIST.

28:51.480 --> 28:52.606
[ Laughing ] NO.

28:52.610 --> 28:54.510
Amanda:
CLAIRE? IT'S TIME.

28:54.520 --> 28:56.897
BE RIGHT THERE.

28:56.900 --> 28:59.471
YOUR MOTHER WANTS PICTURES OF
ALL OF YOU IN FRONT OF THE TREE.

28:59.480 --> 29:02.449
[ LAUGHS ] YOU'D THINK THAT
SHE'S RUNNING FOR PRESIDENT.

29:02.450 --> 29:03.769
OH,
ANOTHER EIGHT YEARS,

29:03.780 --> 29:05.611
BUT FOR NOW,
WE'LL SETTLE FOR V.P.

29:05.620 --> 29:07.315
WHAT -- IS SHE
ON THE SHORT LIST?

29:07.320 --> 29:09.732
DID YOU THINK
THIS WAS JUST AN OPEN HOUSE?

29:09.740 --> 29:11.822
DOES MY DAD KNOW?

29:11.830 --> 29:13.912
YOUR FATHER IS
ABOUT TO BECOME THE HUSBAND

29:13.920 --> 29:15.820
OF THE MOST POWERFUL WOMAN
IN AMERICA,

29:15.830 --> 29:18.037
SO I THINK
HE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

29:20.370 --> 29:22.372
Miranda: ALL CLEAR.
THERE ARE NO BOMBS HERE.

29:22.380 --> 29:23.460
HE NEEDS TO GIVE US
SOME MORE INFORMATION.

29:23.470 --> 29:25.256
WE'RE RUNNING OUT OF PLACES
TO SEARCH.

29:25.260 --> 29:26.796
I KNOW
YOU KNOW WHERE IT IS.

29:26.800 --> 29:27.869
I DON'T. I SWEAR.

29:27.880 --> 29:29.427
SIMON, THINK.

29:29.430 --> 29:30.886
WHERE COULD IT BE?

29:30.890 --> 29:32.187
I REMEMBER
WHEN I SAW THE PLANS

29:32.190 --> 29:33.589
FOR THE TRAIN STATIONS
IN NEW YORK,

29:33.600 --> 29:35.477
THE TAN KS THAT FUEL
THE BACKUP GENERATORS

29:35.480 --> 29:37.186
AT GRAND CENTRAL
ARE HERE.

29:37.190 --> 29:38.305
THEY'RE UNDER
THIS BUILDING.

29:38.310 --> 29:39.265
THE DOGS HAVE BEEN
ALL THROUGH THE BUILDING.

29:39.270 --> 29:40.555
THEY FOUND NOTHING.

29:40.560 --> 29:42.232
IT MUST BE SOMEWHERE
WHERE THEY CAN'T SMELL IT.

29:42.240 --> 29:45.061
I KEEP THINKING ABOUT
THAT BRAIDED COPPER WIRE.

29:45.070 --> 29:47.982
WHY USE THAT INSTEAD OF
THE BLASTING WIRE, LIKE AT GCT?

29:47.990 --> 29:49.605
BRAIDED COPPER --
IT'S NON-CORROSIVE.

29:49.610 --> 29:51.862
IT'S DESIGNED TO WITHSTAND
EXTREME TEMPERATURES --

29:51.870 --> 29:53.360
FIRE, HEAT, COLD, WATER.

29:53.370 --> 29:55.702
THE EDC TEAMS WOULDN'T BE ABLE
TO DETECT A BOMB

29:55.710 --> 29:56.995
IF IT WAS SUBMERGED.

29:57.000 --> 29:58.490
BUT WE'RE NOWHERE NEAR WATER.

29:58.500 --> 30:01.048
WHERE'S THE BOILER ROOM?

30:01.050 --> 30:02.256
CAN YOU HOLD THAT
FOR A SECOND?

30:02.260 --> 30:03.830
OPEN IT UP NOW!

30:07.970 --> 30:10.370
[ BEEPING ]

30:12.850 --> 30:14.340
CAN YOU DEFUSE IT?

30:14.350 --> 30:16.227
WE FOUND IT. AND GUESS
WHAT ELSE IS DOWN HERE.

30:16.230 --> 30:17.879
10,000 gallons of diesel.

30:17.890 --> 30:19.380
Which means
we're gonna have to clear

30:19.390 --> 30:21.108
A LOT MORE
THAN JUST THIS BUILDING.

30:21.110 --> 30:22.486
TAKE ELIAS
BACK TO THE COMMAND CENTER

30:22.490 --> 30:23.775
SO THEY CAN TAKE HIM
INTO CUSTODY.

30:25.240 --> 30:26.605
HEY, HEY! HEY!

30:26.610 --> 30:29.317
GO WITH THEM, ELIAS --
PLEASE.

30:29.320 --> 30:32.778
WHEN THEY FIRST CALLED ME,
I THOUGHT I HAD NO CHOICE.

30:32.790 --> 30:34.246
BUT THAT'S NOT THE TRUTH.

30:35.870 --> 30:37.531
I WAS JUST TOO SCARED
TO MAKE IT.

30:37.540 --> 30:39.030
ELIAS.

30:39.040 --> 30:40.871
ELIAS.

30:40.880 --> 30:42.416
I'M NOT SCARED ANYMORE.

30:42.420 --> 30:43.409
ELIAS, DON'T.

30:43.420 --> 30:44.830
HEY! NO!

30:50.260 --> 30:51.591
HOW BAD IS IT IN THERE?
ARE THEY SINGING YET?

30:51.600 --> 30:53.090
[ SIGHS ] I WOULDN'T KNOW.
I'M LEAVING.

30:53.100 --> 30:55.421
AT LEAST, I WOULD IF I COULD GET
A DAMN UBER TO SHOW UP.

30:55.430 --> 30:57.261
IN D.C.
ON NEW YEAR'S EVE?

30:57.270 --> 30:58.806
YOU'RE BETTER OFF
GOING INSIDE

30:58.810 --> 31:00.971
AND DEBATING THE MERITS OF TRUMP
WITH CLAIRE HAAS.

31:00.980 --> 31:02.686
[ SIGHS ]
RYAN'S IN THERE.

31:05.900 --> 31:07.606
I THOUGHT HE WAS IN LA.

31:07.610 --> 31:11.614
YEAH, WELL, APPARENTLY, L.A. IS
A LOT CLOSER THAN WE THOUGHT.

31:11.620 --> 31:14.248
I KNOW YOU DON'T LIKE
WHAT HE DID,

31:14.250 --> 31:17.651
BUT IF YOU'RE GONNA HATE ANYONE,
HATE ME.

31:17.660 --> 31:19.287
IT'S MY FAULT.
I MADE HIM LIE TO YOU.

31:19.290 --> 31:21.201
THAT'S NOT WHO HE IS.

31:21.210 --> 31:24.043
THAT MAN IN THERE
TAKES BULLETS

31:24.050 --> 31:26.371
FOR THE PEOPLE
HE CARES ABOUT.

31:26.380 --> 31:28.336
I SHOULD KNOW --
HE'S TAKEN SEVERAL FOR ME.

31:28.340 --> 31:30.410
AND HE'D TAKE THEM FOR YOU, TOO,
IF IT EVER COMES TO THAT.

31:30.420 --> 31:33.139
LOOK, I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING IS RIGHT.

31:33.140 --> 31:34.960
I JUST...

31:34.970 --> 31:36.631
I JUST CAN'T TRUST HIM
ANYMORE.

31:36.640 --> 31:38.710
YOU'RE IN THE FBI,
ALEX.

31:38.720 --> 31:41.393
YOU'LL NEVER TRUST ANYONE
AGAIN.

31:41.400 --> 31:43.777
BUT YOU CAN STOP BELIEVING
THAT EVERY DISHONEST THING

31:43.780 --> 31:46.066
THAT SOMEONE DOES
IS THEIR TRUE SELF.

31:46.070 --> 31:48.311
SOME PEOPLE
ARE SIMPLY GOOD.

31:50.110 --> 31:51.281
Caleb: ASK HER, DAD.

31:53.330 --> 31:54.570
CLAIRE --
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:54.580 --> 31:56.320
I'M SORRY. I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO HIM.

31:56.330 --> 31:57.786
WHAT ARE
THOSE NOTES FOR?

31:57.790 --> 32:00.862
I'M GIVING A TOAST
FOR OUR FAMILY AT MIDNIGHT.

32:00.870 --> 32:02.838
IT'S SO NICE
THAT WE'RE ALL HERE TOGETHER.

32:02.840 --> 32:05.161
WHY DON'T YOU TELL HIM
ABOUT THE SHORT LIST?

32:06.460 --> 32:07.495
GO ON -- TELL HIM.

32:09.630 --> 32:11.928
SHELBY,
WHY DON'T YOU AND CALEB...

32:11.930 --> 32:13.090
YEAH, WHY DON'T WE
GIVE THEM A MOMENT?

32:13.100 --> 32:14.715
WHAT? DO YOU --
DO YOU WORK FOR HER NOW?

32:14.720 --> 32:17.097
NO, NO, I-I THINK
THAT MY DAD DESERVES TO KNOW,

32:20.390 --> 32:23.188
THAT THE ONLY REASON
THAT SHE SAID YES

32:23.190 --> 32:26.227
IS BECAUSE SHE'S APPROVED
FOR THE SHORT LIST FOR V.P.

32:26.230 --> 32:28.937
AND THE DNC LOVES A CANDIDATE
WITH STRONG FAMILY VALUES,

32:28.940 --> 32:31.192
AND THE GREAT CLAIRE HAAS
HATES LOSING.

32:36.870 --> 32:38.986
IS THAT TRUE,
CLAIRE?

32:38.990 --> 32:43.370
THE NOMINATION IS --
IS COMPLETELY UNRELATED TO US.

32:43.380 --> 32:44.449
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

32:44.460 --> 32:46.166
THEY'RE READY,
SENATOR.

32:46.170 --> 32:47.706
COME ON.

32:50.040 --> 32:51.928
WHY DID YOU
DO THAT?

32:51.930 --> 32:53.716
B-BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S LIKE TO GROW UP

32:53.720 --> 32:55.347
IN A HOUSE WHERE EVERYBODY LIES
FOR A LIVING.

32:55.350 --> 32:57.341
A-ALL THAT
I'VE EVER TRIED TO DO

32:57.350 --> 32:59.045
IS TO GET THEM
TO TELL THE TRUTH.

32:59.050 --> 33:01.143
AND I AM SO SICK OF WAITING
FOR THAT TO HAPPEN.

33:01.150 --> 33:02.970
[ GLASS CLINKS ]

33:02.980 --> 33:04.356
HELLO, EVERYONE.
GOOD EVENING.

33:04.360 --> 33:06.897
[ GUESTS CHEER ]

33:06.900 --> 33:08.265
I WANT TO THANK YOU ALL

33:08.270 --> 33:10.511
FOR SPENDING THE LAST FEW
MOMENTS OF THIS YEAR

33:10.520 --> 33:11.771
WITH MY FAMILY.

33:11.780 --> 33:13.600
WE'RE SO HAPPY
TO HAVE YOU HERE

33:13.610 --> 33:16.864
AND TO CELEBRATE WHAT HAS BEEN
AN EXTRAORDINARY YEAR

33:16.870 --> 33:18.519
FOR THE DEMOCRATIC PARTY.

33:18.530 --> 33:20.441
HEAR, HEAR!
WHOO!

33:20.450 --> 33:21.997
LET'S DRINK TO THAT.

33:22.000 --> 33:23.615
OF COURSE YOU'RE YOU.

33:23.620 --> 33:25.247
I'M...?

33:25.250 --> 33:27.070
ALEX. YEAH, I JUST DIDN'T --
I DIDN'T PUT IT TOGETHER,

33:27.080 --> 33:28.991
WHICH IS ACTUALLY
PRETTY DUMB OF ME,
IF YOU THINK ABOUT IT,

33:29.000 --> 33:31.332
BECAUSE, "A," YOU TOLD ME
YOU WERE A TRAINEE,

33:31.340 --> 33:33.296
"B," YOU SAID
YOUR NAME WAS ALEX,

33:33.300 --> 33:35.461
AND, "C," WELL, YOU ARE
THE MOST BEAUTIFUL WOMAN HERE,

33:35.470 --> 33:38.337
WHICH SHOULDN'T BUG ME,
BUT WEIRDLY, IT KIND OF DOES.

33:38.340 --> 33:40.467
I'M SORRY.
I JUST REALLY HAVE TO ASK YOU --

33:40.470 --> 33:42.631
ARE YOU AND RYAN STILL MARRIED?
'CAUSE HE TOLD ME --

33:42.640 --> 33:43.720
AT FIRST,
IT WAS AN E-MAIL --

33:43.730 --> 33:45.595
"I THINK
I'M FALLING FOR MY MARK."

33:45.600 --> 33:47.261
AND THEN IT WAS
THE TEXTS AND THE SKYPES

33:47.270 --> 33:49.727
AND THE REALLY LONG
LATE-NIGHT PHONE CALLS

33:49.730 --> 33:51.527
AND THE SECRET, SAD BEERS
DOWN AT THE OLD SETTLER.

33:51.530 --> 33:52.906
AND THEN THE SONG.

33:52.910 --> 33:54.605
YEAH. YEAH,
HE WROTE A SONG ABOUT YOU.

33:54.610 --> 33:55.406
THANK YOU.

33:56.990 --> 33:58.776
AND NOW I'M TRAPPED WITH HIM
DAY AND NIGHT,

33:58.780 --> 34:01.419
AND HE IS STILL TALKING
ALL ABOUT YOU.

34:01.420 --> 34:02.648
AND BECAUSE
HE CAN'T STOP --

34:02.660 --> 34:04.070
BECAUSE HE'S HAD
A LITTLE CHAMPAGNE --

34:04.080 --> 34:05.570
I NOW KNOW
THAT HE THINKS THE FACT

34:05.580 --> 34:08.367
YOU'RE BOTH AT THIS PARTY
IS FATE, KISMET --

34:08.370 --> 34:11.464
SOME SORT OF
"WHEN HARRY MET SALLY..."
ROMANTIC-MOVIE MOMENT.

34:11.470 --> 34:14.257
BUT WHILE HE'S WATCHING
THAT MOVIE, I'M SEEING REALITY,

34:14.260 --> 34:15.545
WHICH IS THAT TOMORROW,

34:15.550 --> 34:17.211
YOU'RE GONNA GO BACK TO QUANTICO
FOR THREE MORE MONTHS,

34:17.220 --> 34:19.461
AND HE'LL BE UNDERCOVER WITH ME
FOR UP TO A YEAR --

34:19.470 --> 34:22.052
STILL TALKING
ALL ABOUT YOU.

34:22.060 --> 34:23.766
I'M REALLY SORRY.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY --
NO, NO, NO, NO.
PLEASE, PLEASE.

34:23.770 --> 34:25.670
THIS ISN'T ABOUT APOLOGIES
OR EXCUSES

34:25.680 --> 34:28.012
OR, LIKE, THE THINGS WE SAY
TO ONE ANOTHER WHEN WE THINK

34:29.850 --> 34:32.523
BECAUSE...
YOU DID DO IT.

34:32.530 --> 34:34.316
YOU BROKE HIS HEART.

34:34.320 --> 34:36.811
AND I KNOW HOW AWFUL THAT IS,
BECAUSE I BROKE IT FIRST.

34:36.820 --> 34:39.641
HE'S ONLY HAD TWO WEEKS
LEARNING TO LIVE WITHOUT YOU.

34:39.650 --> 34:41.902
HE DOES NOT HEAL FAST.

34:41.910 --> 34:43.241
AND NOW YOU WANT
TO BREAK HIM AGAIN

34:43.250 --> 34:45.491
FOR SOME KISS
AT THE END OF A COUNTDOWN?

34:45.500 --> 34:46.535
WHAT HAPPENS TOMORROW?

34:46.540 --> 34:48.952
WHAT HAPPENS AT 12:01?

34:48.960 --> 34:50.655
GIVE HIM A CHANCE
TO PUT HIMSELF BACK TOGETHER

34:50.660 --> 34:52.082
BEFORE YOU BREAK HIM APART
AGAIN.

34:55.760 --> 34:57.910
AND...HAPPY NEW YEAR.

34:59.300 --> 35:00.870
YOU REALLY ARE BEAUTIFUL.

35:00.880 --> 35:01.972
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

35:01.980 --> 35:03.629
[ SIGHS ]

35:03.640 --> 35:05.847
NO RUNNING. NO RUNNING.
JUST KEEP MOVING.

35:05.850 --> 35:09.172
FOLLOW THE FBI DETAIL
OUT THE DOOR AND INTO THE E.C.C.

35:09.180 --> 35:10.556
STAY CALM.
NO NEED TO PANIC.

35:10.560 --> 35:12.937
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

35:12.940 --> 35:14.180
[ BEEPING ]

35:22.580 --> 35:23.990
THEY'RE WORKING
AS FAST AS THEY CAN,

35:24.000 --> 35:25.490
BUT IF THEY CAN'T DEFUSE IT,
WE MIGHT NOT HAVE TIME

35:25.500 --> 35:27.115
to get ourselves out.

35:27.120 --> 35:28.576
TH EY'LL HAVE TIME.

35:28.580 --> 35:30.400
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

35:30.410 --> 35:32.742
I'M SORRY ABOUT ALL THIS.

35:32.750 --> 35:34.832
NO.
WE'RE NOT DOING THAT.

35:42.390 --> 35:43.596
SENATOR HAAS.

35:43.600 --> 35:45.716
I AM SO SORRY.

35:45.720 --> 35:47.426
I REGRETTED IT
THE MOMENT THAT IT HAPPENED.

35:47.430 --> 35:49.011
IT WAS A MISTAKE.

35:49.020 --> 35:51.477
YOU THINK I CARE
THAT YOU SLEPT WITH MY HUSBAND?

35:51.480 --> 35:52.970
HE CAN DO WHAT HE WANTS.

35:52.980 --> 35:55.028
YOU DESTROYED MY SON.

35:55.030 --> 35:57.430
THAT'S UNFORGIVABLE.

35:57.440 --> 36:00.682
AND I PLAN TO MAKE IT
MY BUSINESS TO DESTROY YOU, TOO.

36:04.950 --> 36:06.986
COUNT ALONG WITH ME.

36:06.990 --> 36:09.231
All: 10...

36:09.240 --> 36:11.629
9...

36:11.630 --> 36:14.281
8...

36:14.290 --> 36:16.167
7...

36:16.170 --> 36:18.240
6...

36:18.250 --> 36:21.083
5...

36:21.090 --> 36:22.796
4...

36:22.800 --> 36:25.212
3...

36:25.220 --> 36:27.176
2...

36:27.180 --> 36:29.501
1...

36:29.510 --> 36:31.262
HAPPY NEW YEAR!

36:31.270 --> 36:33.101
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE,
NOISEMAKERS POPPING ]

36:33.110 --> 36:34.065
HEY.

36:36.980 --> 36:38.766
COME ON.
I'LL TAKE YOU BACK.

36:43.320 --> 36:45.447
WE'RE CONFIRMED.

36:45.450 --> 36:46.815
IT'S DEFUSED.

36:46.820 --> 36:47.946
[ SIGHS ]

36:47.950 --> 36:48.939
SIMON.

36:48.950 --> 36:50.941
THEY'VE DEFUSED THE BOMB.
IT'S SAFE.

36:50.950 --> 36:51.746
YOU CAN LET IT GO.

36:53.250 --> 36:54.626
[ SIGHS ]

36:56.880 --> 36:58.825
[ EXPLOSION ]

37:07.100 --> 37:08.965
I JUST WANTED
TO ASK YOU --

37:08.970 --> 37:10.460
WHY DO YOU GIVE US
THOSE CASES?

37:10.470 --> 37:11.937
THEY CAN'T BE SOLVED.

37:11.940 --> 37:14.477
TO REMIND YOU
THAT YOU CAN GATHER

37:14.480 --> 37:17.643
THE SMARTEST, BRAVEST,
MOST COMMITTED PEOPLE,

37:17.650 --> 37:21.108
GIVE THEM THE BEST ADVANTAGES
OF TECHNOLOGY AND INFORMATION,

37:21.110 --> 37:24.614
AND THEY WILL STILL LOSE,
STILL GET OUTWITTED.

37:24.620 --> 37:26.235
THEN WHY KEEP THEM OPEN?

37:26.240 --> 37:28.561
WHY NOT JUST ADMIT
THAT YOU COULDN'T SOLVE THEM?

37:28.570 --> 37:30.652
WHEN THE FBI LOSES,

37:30.660 --> 37:32.912
IT'S DIFFERENT THAN A LOSS
FOR OTHER PEOPLE.

37:32.920 --> 37:35.491
IT MEANS MORE
WHEN THE STAKES ARE SO HIGH,

37:35.500 --> 37:37.741
SO WE DON'T LIKE
TO CALL IT A LOSS.

37:37.750 --> 37:39.490
WE JUST DON'T WANT
TO LOOK AT IT THAT WAY.

37:39.500 --> 37:43.459
YOU DON'T THINK IT'S WRONG
TO NOT ADMIT DEFEAT,

37:43.470 --> 37:47.088
NOT ACCEPT
YOUR WEAKNESSES?

37:47.090 --> 37:48.637
OH, YEAH. I DO.

37:48.640 --> 37:49.959
BUT I DON'T MAKE
THE RULES.

37:51.220 --> 37:54.769
BETWEEN ME AND YOU

37:54.770 --> 37:56.556
I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT...

37:56.560 --> 37:59.973
I DON'T FEEL LIKE
GOING BACK IN THERE RIGHT NOW.

37:59.980 --> 38:02.153
TAKE ME SOMEWHERE?

38:02.160 --> 38:03.149
WHERE?

38:03.160 --> 38:04.309
BETWEEN ME AND YOU

38:04.320 --> 38:05.810
ANYWHERE.

38:05.820 --> 38:08.106
I DON'T THINK I'M READY
TO ACCEPT DEFEAT RIGHT NOW,

38:08.110 --> 38:12.365
AND -- AND GOING BACK IN THERE
WOULD...

38:12.370 --> 38:13.997
IT WOULD FEEL LIKE THAT.

38:15.330 --> 38:16.706
I'M YOUR TEACHER.

38:16.710 --> 38:18.166
I KNOW.

38:18.170 --> 38:20.570
TEACH ME SOMETHING.

38:22.050 --> 38:23.677
THE FUTURE

38:27.050 --> 38:28.335
BETWEEN ME AND YOU

38:28.340 --> 38:30.547
WELL, YOU LEI-T
WITHOUT SAYING GOODBYE.

38:30.550 --> 38:33.269
I, UM, I GOT A RIDE HOME
WITH VASQUEZ.

38:33.270 --> 38:35.090
SHE WANTED TO WORK ON HER CASE
SOME MORE.

38:35.100 --> 38:37.011
ARE YOU MAD AT ME
ABOUT SOMETHING?

38:37.020 --> 38:39.511
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT YOU DID?

38:39.520 --> 38:43.524
I TOLD YOU THAT I WASN'T GONNA
SURROUND YOU WITH FAMILY,

38:43.530 --> 38:46.738
AND THEN
I SURROUNDED YOU WITH FAMILY.

38:46.740 --> 38:49.607
CALEB,
I LIKE YOUR FAMILY.

38:49.610 --> 38:53.159
AND THEY ARE TRYING
REALLY HARD.

38:53.160 --> 38:55.537
BUT YOU JUST HAD TO
REACH IN THERE AND DESTROY IT.

38:55.540 --> 38:57.030
AND WHY?

38:57.040 --> 38:58.860
WHAT --
BECAUSE THEY HAVE HOPE?

38:58.870 --> 39:00.531
BECAUSE THEY'RE LYING
TO EACH OTHER.

39:00.540 --> 39:01.871
WHO CARES?

39:01.880 --> 39:05.418
WHO CARES IF YOUR MOM
IS USING YOUR DAD?

39:05.420 --> 39:07.456
LOOK, YOU ALWAYS SAID
THAT HE WANTED ANOTHER CHANCE.

39:07.460 --> 39:08.415
NOW HE'S GETTING ONE.

39:08.420 --> 39:10.047
AND MAYBE --

39:10.050 --> 39:12.132
MAYBE SHE HAS TO TELL HERSELF
IT'S ABOUT POLITICS

39:12.140 --> 39:13.960
BECAUSE IT'S TOO PAINFUL
TO ADMIT

39:13.970 --> 39:16.803
THAT SHE STILL LOVES HIM
Al-TER EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED.

39:16.810 --> 39:18.050
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

39:18.060 --> 39:19.766
AND IT IS NOT YOUR PLACE

39:19.770 --> 39:22.398
TO REACH IN THERE
AND SCREW WITH THEIR PROCESS --

39:22.400 --> 39:25.733
JUST LIKE IT IS NOT YOUR PLACE
TO GO BEHIND MY BACK

39:25.740 --> 39:28.311
AND GIVE SAMAR'S NUMBER
TO THE FBI.

39:28.320 --> 39:30.470
YOU MEAN THE GIRL
THAT WAS CONNING YOU FOR YEARS?

39:30.480 --> 39:33.153
SO YOU SHOULD HAVE TOLD ME
AND LET ME DEAL WITH IT,

39:33.160 --> 39:34.980
RATHER THAN
FORCING ME TO.

39:34.990 --> 39:37.538
YEAH, BUT PEOPLE
NEED TO KNOW THE TRUTH.

39:37.540 --> 39:39.485
THAT'S WHY
WE'RE HERE.

39:39.490 --> 39:42.493
"THE FBI RAIDED THE SAFE HOUSE
OF FOUR SISTEMICS MEMBERS

39:42.500 --> 39:44.331
IN FRANKFORT, KENTUCKY,
THIS MORNING --

39:44.340 --> 39:46.911
HOURS BEFORE THEIR PLANNED
SUICIDE BOMB ATTACK

39:46.920 --> 39:48.410
ON THE STATE SUPREME COURT

39:48.420 --> 39:50.877
DURING THE OPENING REMARKS
IN THE SISTEMICS' TRIAL.

39:50.880 --> 39:54.304
THE RAID WAS LED BY
A SPECIAL AGENT CLAYTON HAAS."

39:54.310 --> 39:56.710
LOOK, I TOLD YOU --
THEY BRAINWASHED ME. ALL RIGHT?

39:56.720 --> 39:58.005
THEY MADE ME BELIEVE

39:58.010 --> 39:59.762
THAT THE GOVERNMENT WAS
TAKING AWAY OUR LIBERTIES.

39:59.770 --> 40:02.068
BUT I -- I WAS 17!

40:02.070 --> 40:03.606
I WAS JUST A KID!

40:03.610 --> 40:04.679
AND WHAT?

40:04.690 --> 40:06.146
YOU THOUGHT
IF YOU BLEW YOURSELF UP

40:06.150 --> 40:07.720
IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE COURTHOUSE,

40:07.730 --> 40:09.721
YOU WOULD SHOW PEOPLE
THE TRUTH?

40:09.730 --> 40:11.948
FOR SO LONG,
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO REALIZE

40:11.950 --> 40:15.613
WHY I'VE NEVER TOLD YOU
THAT I LOVE YOU.

40:15.620 --> 40:16.939
BECAUSE I DO.

40:16.950 --> 40:19.191
CALEB,
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

40:19.200 --> 40:20.736
BUT I KNOW
THAT YOU'LL HURT ME --

40:20.740 --> 40:22.799
AGAIN AND AGAIN,

40:22.800 --> 40:25.246
REGARDLESS
OF WHETHER IT'S RIGHT TO,

40:25.250 --> 40:27.798
BECAUSE YOU ARE WILLING
TO BLOW THINGS UP

40:27.800 --> 40:30.246
JUST TO GET PEOPLE
TO SEE YOUR TRUTH,

40:30.250 --> 40:33.048
INSTEAD OF HELPING THEM
FIND IT FOR THEMSELVES.

40:33.050 --> 40:36.099
BUT I'M DOING MY BEST

40:36.100 --> 40:37.636
ARE YOU
BREAKING UP WITH ME?

40:37.640 --> 40:40.177
I'M SORRY.

40:40.180 --> 40:42.683
CALEB, I-I'M DONE
GETTING HURT BY YOU.

40:42.690 --> 40:43.475
BY ANYONE.

40:43.480 --> 40:45.141
I'M DONE.

40:53.570 --> 40:55.060
[ SIGHS ]

41:00.530 --> 41:02.282
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

41:02.290 --> 41:03.496
CHARLIE!

41:03.500 --> 41:04.740
CHARLIE!

41:04.750 --> 41:07.036
[ STAMMERS ]
CHARLIE!

41:07.040 --> 41:08.667
CHARLIE,
WHO DID THIS TO YOU?

41:08.670 --> 41:10.206
[ GROANS SOl-TLY ]

41:10.210 --> 41:12.383
[ Dialing, ringing ]

41:12.390 --> 41:13.846
DISPATCHER:
911. What's your emergency?

41:13.850 --> 41:15.579
YES,
I NEED AN AMBULANCE.

41:15.590 --> 41:17.888
I'll send one.
YES, NOW, PLEASE.

41:17.890 --> 41:19.630
Are you at Anacostia Lane?

41:19.640 --> 41:21.688
[Voice breaking ] YES,
THAT'S WHERE I'M CALLING FROM.

41:21.690 --> 41:22.896
Just stay calm, ma'am.

41:24.980 --> 41:26.720
Ma'am?
Are you still there?

41:26.730 --> 41:28.391
I'M SO SORRY.

41:28.400 --> 41:30.550
I'M SO SORRY
I DIDN'T BELIEVE IN YOU.

41:30.560 --> 41:31.811
[ SOBS ]

41:31.820 --> 41:34.027
[ HORNS HONKING ]

41:36.240 --> 41:38.151
SO GOOD
TO FINALLY MEET YOU.

41:38.160 --> 41:39.946
WE EXPECTED YOU
A FEW WEEKS AGO.

41:39.950 --> 41:41.577
I COULDN'T MAKE IT,
BUT I'M HERE NOW.

41:41.580 --> 41:42.911
WONDERFUL.

41:42.920 --> 41:44.239
WE HAVE THE VAULT OPEN
SO YOU CAN SEE

41:44.250 --> 41:46.377
THE SAFETY DEPOSIT BOXES,
AS REQUESTED,

41:46.380 --> 41:48.029
AND DECIDE
WHICH MEET YOUR NEEDS.

41:48.040 --> 41:49.667
SHOW ME THE FOUR BIGGEST
YOU GUYS HAVE.

41:49.670 --> 41:51.114
OKAY.

41:51.120 --> 41:53.884
BEAUTIFUL SPACE --
SO CLOSE TO GRAND CENTRAL.

41:54.840 --> 41:56.967
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

41:56.970 --> 41:59.256
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
WERE THERE TWO BOMBS?

41:59.260 --> 42:00.579
OR THE BOMB IN THE HOTEL
WAS A DECOY

42:00.590 --> 42:02.182
AND ELIAS
WAS DISTRACTING US

42:02.190 --> 42:03.509
SO HE COULD SET
HIS REAL PLAN IN MOTION.

42:03.520 --> 42:05.681
BUT WHAT WAS HIS PLAN?
WHAT BLEW UP?

42:05.690 --> 42:07.226
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

42:07.230 --> 42:08.185
MOVE!

42:11.820 --> 42:13.981
Alex: OH, MY GOD.
THE COMMAND CENTER.

42:16.860 --> 42:18.987
[Voice breaking ]
WHO WAS INSIDE, ALEX?

42:18.990 --> 42:20.446
WAS EVERYONE INSIDE?

42:20.450 --> 42:22.748
[ SIRENS WAILING ]
